  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: "  Book One (Psalms 1\u201341)"
      content: '  Oh, the joys of those who do notfollow the advice of the wicked,or
        stand around with sinners,or join in with mockers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But they delight in the law of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,meditating
        on it day and night.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are like trees planted along the riverbank,bearing fruit each
        season.Their leaves never wither,and they prosper in all they do.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But not the wicked!They are like worthless chaff, scattered by the
        wind.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will be condemned at the time of judgment.Sinners will have
        no place among the godly.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Why are the nations so angry?Why do they waste their time with
        futile plans?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The kings of the earth prepare for battle;the rulers plot togetheragainst
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and against his anointed one.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLet us break their chains,\u201D they cry,\u201Cand free ourselves
        from slavery to God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the one who rules in heaven laughs.The Lord scoffs at them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then in anger he rebukes them,terrifying them with his fierce fury.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the Lord declares, \u201CI have placed my chosen king on the
        thronein Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]] on my holy mountain.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>on Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "The king proclaims the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s decree:\u201CThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u2018You are my son.[[COMMENT(0)]]Today
        I have become your Father.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:7a '
        content: Or <b>Son; </b>also in 2:12.
      - number: '2:7b '
        content: Or <b>Today I reveal you as my son.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Only ask, and I will give you the nations as your inheritance,the
        whole earth as your possession.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will break[[COMMENT(0)]] them with an iron rodand smash them
        like clay pots.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:9 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>rule. </b>Compare Rev 2:27.
    - title: 
      content: 'Now then, you kings, act wisely!Be warned, you rulers of the earth!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with reverent fear,and rejoice
        with trembling.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm of David, regarding the time David fled from his son Absalom. 
        O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I have so many enemies;so many are against
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So many are saying,\u201CGod will never rescue him!\u201D Interlude[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Selah. </b>The meaning of this word is uncertain, though
          it is probably a musical or literary term. It is rendered <b>Interlude
          </b>throughout the Psalms.
    - title: 
      content: 'But you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, are a shield around me;you
        are my glory, the one who holds my head high.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and he answered me
        from his holy mountain. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I lay down and slept,yet I woke up in safety,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was watching over me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am not afraid of ten thousand enemieswho surround me on every side.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Arise, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Rescue me, my God!Slap all my
        enemies in the face!Shatter the teeth of the wicked!  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of David, to be accompanied by stringed
        instruments.  Answer me when I call to you,O God who declares me innocent.Free
        me from my troubles.Have mercy on me and hear my prayer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How long will you people ruin my reputation?How long will you make
        groundless accusations?How long will you continue your lies? Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You can be sure of this:The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> set apart
        the godly for himself.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will answer when I
        call to him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t sin by letting anger control you.Think about it overnight
        and remain silent. Interlude  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Offer sacrifices in the right spirit,and trust the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Many people say, \u201CWho will show us better times?\u201DLet your
        face smile on us, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have given me greater joythan those who have abundant harvests
        of grain and new wine.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of David, to be accompanied by the
        flute.  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, hear me as I pray;pay attention to
        my groaning.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen to my cry for help, my King and my God,for I pray to no one
        but you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen to my voice in the morning, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Each
        morning I bring my requests to you and wait expectantly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O God, you take no pleasure in wickedness;you cannot tolerate the
        sins of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, the proud may not stand in your presence,for you hate
        all who do evil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will destroy those who tell lies.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        detests murderers and deceivers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because of your unfailing love, I can enter your house;I will worship
        at your Temple with deepest awe.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lead me in the right path, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,or my enemies
        will conquer me.Make your way plain for me to follow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My enemies cannot speak a truthful word.Their deepest desire is to
        destroy others.Their talk is foul, like the stench from an open grave.Their
        tongues are filled with flattery.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:9 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>with lies. </b>Compare Rom 3:13.
    - title: 
      content: 'O God, declare them guilty.Let them be caught in their own traps.Drive
        them away because of their many sins,for they have rebelled against you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But let all who take refuge in you rejoice;let them sing joyful praises
        forever.Spread your protection over them,that all who love your name may
        be filled with joy.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm of David, to be accompanied by an
        eight-stringed instrument.[[COMMENT(0)]]  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        don\u2019t rebuke me in your angeror discipline me in your rage.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>with stringed instruments; according to the sheminith.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Have compassion on me, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for I am weak.Heal
        me, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for my bones are in agony.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am sick at heart.How long, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, until
        you restore me?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Return, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and rescue me.Save me because
        of your unfailing love.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the dead do not remember you.Who can praise you from the grave?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>from Sheol?</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I am worn out from sobbing.All night I flood my bed with weeping,drenching
        it with my tears.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My vision is blurred by grief;my eyes are worn out because of all
        my enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Go away, all you who do evil,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has heard my weeping.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has heard my plea;the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will answer my prayer.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of David, which he sang to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        concerning Cush of the tribe of Benjamin.  I come to you for protection,
        O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God.Save me from my persecutors\u2014rescue
        me!  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>A shiggaion, </b>probably indicating a musical setting
          for the psalm.
    - title: 
      content: "If you don\u2019t, they will maul me like a lion,tearing me to pieces
        with no one to rescue me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God, if I have done wrongor am guilty
        of injustice,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'if I have betrayed a friendor plundered my enemy without cause,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then let my enemies capture me.Let them trample me into the groundand
        drag my honor in the dust. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Arise, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, in anger!Stand up against the
        fury of my enemies!Wake up, my God, and bring justice!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Gather the nations before you.Rule over them from on high.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> judges the nations.Declare me righteous,
        O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,for I am innocent, O Most High!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'End the evil of those who are wicked,and defend the righteous.For
        you look deep within the mind and heart,O righteous God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God is my shield,saving those whose hearts are true and right.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God is an honest judge.He is angry with the wicked every day.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If a person does not repent,God[[COMMENT(0)]] will sharpen his sword;he
        will bend and string his bow.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>he.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'He will prepare his deadly weaponsand shoot his flaming arrows.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked conceive evil;they are pregnant with troubleand give birth
        to lies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They dig a deep pit to trap others,then fall into it themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The trouble they make for others backfires on them.The violence they
        plan falls on their own heads.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of David, to be accompanied by a
        stringed instrument.[[COMMENT(0)]]  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, our Lord,
        your majestic name fills the earth!Your glory is higher than the heavens.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>according to the gittith.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'You have taught children and infantsto tell of your strength,[[COMMENT(0)]]silencing
        your enemiesand all who oppose you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:2 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>to give you praise. </b>Compare Matt 21:16.
    - title: 
      content: "When I look at the night sky and see the work of your fingers\u2014the
        moon and the stars you set in place\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'what are mere mortals that you should think about them,human beings
        that you should care for them?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>what is man that you should think of him, / the son of
          man that you should care for him?</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet you made them only a little lower than God[[COMMENT(0)]]and crowned
        them[[COMMENT(1)]] with glory and honor.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:5a '
        content: Or <b>Yet you made them only a little lower than the angels; </b>Hebrew
          reads <b>Yet you made him </b>[i.e., man] <b>a little lower than Elohim.</b>
      - number: '8:5b '
        content: Hebrew <b>him </b>[i.e., man]; similarly in 8:6.
    - title: 
      content: "You gave them charge of everything you made,putting all things under
        their authority\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the flocks and the herdsand all the wild animals,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the birds in the sky, the fish in the sea,and everything that swims
        the ocean currents.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm of David, to be sung to the tune
        \u201CDeath of the Son.\u201D  I will praise you, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        with all my heart;I will tell of all the marvelous things you have done.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will be filled with joy because of you.I will sing praises to your
        name, O Most High.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My enemies retreated;they staggered and died when you appeared.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For you have judged in my favor;from your throne you have judged
        with fairness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have rebuked the nations and destroyed the wicked;you have erased
        their names forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The enemy is finished, in endless ruins;the cities you uprooted are
        now forgotten.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> reigns forever,executing judgment
        from his throne.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will judge the world with justiceand rule the nations with fairness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is a shelter for the oppressed,a
        refuge in times of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who know your name trust in you,for you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        do not abandon those who search for you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sing praises to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who reigns in Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]Tell
        the world about his unforgettable deeds.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion; </b>also in 9:14.
    - title: 
      content: 'For he who avenges murder cares for the helpless.He does not ignore
        the cries of those who suffer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have mercy on me.See how my enemies
        torment me.Snatch me back from the jaws of death.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Save me so I can praise you publicly at Jerusalem\u2019s gates,so
        I can rejoice that you have rescued me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The nations have fallen into the pit they dug for others.Their own
        feet have been caught in the trap they set.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is known for his justice.The wicked
        are trapped by their own deeds. Quiet Interlude[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Higgaion Selah. </b>The meaning of this phrase is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked will go down to the grave.[[COMMENT(0)]]This is the fate
        of all the nations who ignore God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:17 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But the needy will not be ignored forever;the hopes of the poor will
        not always be crushed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Arise, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Do not let mere mortals defy
        you!Judge the nations!  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, why do you stand so far away?Why
        do you hide when I am in trouble?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked arrogantly hunt down the poor.Let them be caught in the
        evil they plan for others.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For they brag about their evil desires;they praise the greedy and
        curse the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked are too proud to seek God.They seem to think that God
        is dead.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet they succeed in everything they do.They do not see your punishment
        awaiting them.They sneer at all their enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They think, \u201CNothing bad will ever happen to us!We will be free
        of trouble forever!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their mouths are full of cursing, lies, and threats.[[COMMENT(0)]]Trouble
        and evil are on the tips of their tongues.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:7 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>cursing and bitterness. </b>Compare Rom 3:14.
    - title: 
      content: 'They lurk in ambush in the villages,waiting to murder innocent people.They
        are always searching for helpless victims.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Like lions crouched in hiding,they wait to pounce on the helpless.Like
        hunters they capture the helplessand drag them away in nets.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their helpless victims are crushed;they fall beneath the strength
        of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The wicked think, \u201CGod isn\u2019t watching us!He has closed
        his eyes and won\u2019t even see what we do!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Arise, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Punish the wicked, O God!Do
        not ignore the helpless!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why do the wicked get away with despising God?They think, \u201CGod
        will never call us to account.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you see the trouble and grief they cause.You take note of it
        and punish them.The helpless put their trust in you.You defend the orphans.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Break the arms of these wicked, evil people!Go after them until the
        last one is destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is king forever and ever!The godless
        nations will vanish from the land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you know the hopes of the helpless.Surely
        you will hear their cries and comfort them.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm of David.  I trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        for protection.So why do you say to me,\u201CFly like a bird to the mountains
        for safety!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked are stringing their bowsand fitting their arrows on the
        bowstrings.They shoot from the shadowsat those whose hearts are right.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The foundations of law and order have collapsed.What can the righteous
        do?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is in his holy Temple;the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        still rules from heaven.He watches everyone closely,examining every person
        on earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> examines both the righteous and the
        wicked.He hates those who love violence.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will rain down blazing coals and burning sulfur on the wicked,punishing
        them with scorching winds.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of David, to be accompanied by an
        eight-stringed instrument.[[COMMENT(0)]]  Help, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        for the godly are fast disappearing!The faithful have vanished from the earth!  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>according to the sheminith.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Neighbors lie to each other,speaking with flattering lips and deceitful
        hearts.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> cut off their flattering lipsand
        silence their boastful tongues.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They say, \u201CWe will lie to our hearts\u2019 content.Our lips
        are our own\u2014who can stop us?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> replies, \u201CI have seen violence
        done to the helpless,and I have heard the groans of the poor.Now I will rise
        up to rescue them,as they have longed for me to do.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s promises are pure,like silver
        refined in a furnace,purified seven times over.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, we know you will protect
        the oppressed,preserving them forever from this lying generation,  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of David.  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        how long will you forget me? Forever?How long will you look the other way?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How long must I struggle with anguish in my soul,with sorrow in my
        heart every day?How long will my enemy have the upper hand?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Turn and answer me, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God!Restore
        the sparkle to my eyes, or I will die.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let my enemies gloat, saying, \u201CWe have defeated him!\u201DDon\u2019t
        let them rejoice at my downfall.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I trust in your unfailing love.I will rejoice because you have
        rescued me.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm of David.  Only fools say in their
        hearts,\u201CThere is no God.\u201DThey are corrupt, and their actions are
        evil;not one of them does good!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> looks down from heavenon the entire
        human race;he looks to see if anyone is truly wise,if anyone seeks God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But no, all have turned away;all have become corrupt.[[COMMENT(0)]]No
        one does good,not a single one!  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:3 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>have become useless. </b>Compare Rom 3:12.
    - title: 
      content: "Will those who do evil never learn?They eat up my people like breadand
        wouldn\u2019t think of praying to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Terror will grip them,for God is with those who obey him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked frustrate the plans of the oppressed,but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will protect his people.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm of David.  Who may worship in your sanctuary, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?Who
        may enter your presence on your holy hill?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who lead blameless lives and do what is right,speaking the
        truth from sincere hearts.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who refuse to gossipor harm their neighborsor speak evil of
        their friends.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who despise flagrant sinners,and honor the faithful followers
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and keep their promises even when it hurts.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of David.  Keep me safe, O God,for I have come
        to you for refuge.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>miktam. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: "I said to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CYou are my Master!Every
        good thing I have comes from you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godly people in the landare my true heroes!I take pleasure in
        them!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Troubles multiply for those who chase after other gods.I will not
        take part in their sacrifices of bloodor even speak the names of their gods.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you alone are my inheritance, my cup
        of blessing.You guard all that is mine.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The land you have given me is a pleasant land.What a wonderful inheritance!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will bless the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who guides me;even at
        night my heart instructs me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is always with me.I will not
        be shaken, for he is right beside me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No wonder my heart is glad, and I rejoice.[[COMMENT(0)]]My body rests
        in safety.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:9 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>and my tongue shouts his praises. </b>Compare
          Acts 2:26.
    - title: 
      content: 'For you will not leave my soul among the dead[[COMMENT(0)]]or allow
        your holy one[[COMMENT(1)]] to rot in the grave.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:10a '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Sheol.</b>
      - number: '16:10b '
        content: Or <b>your Holy One.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A prayer of David.  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, hear my plea for
        justice.Listen to my cry for help.Pay attention to my prayer,for it comes
        from honest lips.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Declare me innocent,for you see those who do right.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have tested my thoughts and examined my heart in the night.You
        have scrutinized me and found nothing wrong.I am determined not to sin in
        what I say.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have followed your commands,which keep me from following cruel
        and evil people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My steps have stayed on your path;I have not wavered from following
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am praying to you because I know you will answer, O God.Bend down
        and listen as I pray.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Show me your unfailing love in wonderful ways.By your mighty power
        you rescuethose who seek refuge from their enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Guard me as you would guard your own eyes.[[COMMENT(0)]]Hide me in
        the shadow of your wings.  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>as the pupil of your eye.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Protect me from wicked people who attack me,from murderous enemies
        who surround me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are without pity.Listen to their boasting!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They track me down and surround me,watching for the chance to throw
        me to the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are like hungry lions, eager to tear me apart\u2014like young
        lions hiding in ambush.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Arise, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Stand against them, and bring
        them to their knees!Rescue me from the wicked with your sword!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'By the power of your hand, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,destroy
        those who look to this world for their reward.But satisfy the hunger of your
        treasured ones.May their children have plenty,leaving an inheritance for
        their descendants.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of David, the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        He sang this song to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> on the day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        rescued him from all his enemies and from Saul. He sang:  I love you, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;you
        are my strength.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is my rock, my fortress, and my savior;my
        God is my rock, in whom I find protection.He is my shield, the power that
        saves me,and my place of safety.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I called on the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who is worthy of praise,and
        he saved me from my enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The ropes of death entangled me;floods of destruction swept over
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The grave[[COMMENT(0)]] wrapped its ropes around me;death laid a
        trap in my path.  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But in my distress I cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;yes,
        I prayed to my God for help.He heard me from his sanctuary;my cry to him
        reached his ears.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the earth quaked and trembled.The foundations of the mountains
        shook;they quaked because of his anger.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Smoke poured from his nostrils;fierce flames leaped from his mouth.Glowing
        coals blazed forth from him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He opened the heavens and came down;dark storm clouds were beneath
        his feet.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Mounted on a mighty angelic being,[[COMMENT(0)]] he flew,soaring
        on the wings of the wind.  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>a cherub.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'He shrouded himself in darkness,veiling his approach with dark rain
        clouds.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Thick clouds shielded the brightness around himand rained down hail
        and burning coals.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:12 '
        content: Or <b>and lightning bolts; </b>also in 18:13.
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> thundered from heaven;the voice of
        the Most High resoundedamid the hail and burning coals.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He shot his arrows and scattered his enemies;great bolts of lightning
        flashed, and they were confused.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then at your command, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,at the blast
        of your breath,the bottom of the sea could be seen,and the foundations of
        the earth were laid bare.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He reached down from heaven and rescued me;he drew me out of deep
        waters.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He rescued me from my powerful enemies,from those who hated me and
        were too strong for me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They attacked me at a moment when I was in distress,but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        supported me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He led me to a place of safety;he rescued me because he delights
        in me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rewarded me for doing right;he restored
        me because of my innocence.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I have kept the ways of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;I have
        not turned from my God to follow evil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have followed all his regulations;I have never abandoned his decrees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am blameless before God;I have kept myself from sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rewarded me for doing right.He has
        seen my innocence.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'To the faithful you show yourself faithful;to those with integrity
        you show integrity.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'To the pure you show yourself pure,but to the crooked you show yourself
        shrewd.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You rescue the humble,but you humiliate the proud.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You light a lamp for me.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, my God,
        lights up my darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In your strength I can crush an army;with my God I can scale any
        wall.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God\u2019s way is perfect.All the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        promises prove true.He is a shield for all who look to him for protection.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For who is God except the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?Who but our
        God is a solid rock?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God arms me with strength,and he makes my way perfect.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He makes me as surefooted as a deer,enabling me to stand on mountain
        heights.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He trains my hands for battle;he strengthens my arm to draw a bronze
        bow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have given me your shield of victory.Your right hand supports
        me;your help[[COMMENT(0)]] has made me great.  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:35 '
        content: Hebrew <b>your humility; </b>compare 2 Sam 22:36.
    - title: 
      content: 'You have made a wide path for my feetto keep them from slipping.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I chased my enemies and caught them;I did not stop until they were
        conquered.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I struck them down so they could not get up;they fell beneath my
        feet.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have armed me with strength for the battle;you have subdued my
        enemies under my feet.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You placed my foot on their necks.I have destroyed all who hated
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They called for help, but no one came to their rescue.They even cried
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, but he refused to answer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I ground them as fine as dust in the wind.I swept them into the gutter
        like dirt.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You gave me victory over my accusers.You appointed me ruler over
        nations;people I don\u2019t even know now serve me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As soon as they hear of me, they submit;foreign nations cringe before
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They all lose their courageand come trembling from their strongholds.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives! Praise to my Rock!May the
        God of my salvation be exalted!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He is the God who pays back those who harm me;he subdues the nations
        under me  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and rescues me from my enemies.You hold me safe beyond the reach
        of my enemies;you save me from violent opponents.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For this, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I will praise you among
        the nations;I will sing praises to your name.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of David.  The heavens proclaim the
        glory of God.The skies display his craftsmanship.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Day after day they continue to speak;night after night they make
        him known.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They speak without a sound or word;their voice is never heard.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:3 '
        content: Or <b>There is no speech or language where their voice is not heard.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet their message has gone throughout the earth,and their words to
        all the world.God has made a home in the heavens for the sun.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It bursts forth like a radiant bridegroom after his wedding.It rejoices
        like a great athlete eager to run the race.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The sun rises at one end of the heavensand follows its course to
        the other end.Nothing can hide from its heat.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The instructions of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> are perfect,reviving
        the soul.The decrees of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> are trustworthy,making
        wise the simple.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The commandments of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> are right,bringing
        joy to the heart.The commands of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> are clear,giving
        insight for living.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Reverence for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is pure,lasting forever.The
        laws of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> are true;each one is fair.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are more desirable than gold,even the finest gold.They are sweeter
        than honey,even honey dripping from the comb.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are a warning to your servant,a great reward for those who obey
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How can I know all the sins lurking in my heart?Cleanse me from these
        hidden faults.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Keep your servant from deliberate sins!Don\u2019t let them control
        me.Then I will be free of guiltand innocent of great sin.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of David.  In times of trouble, may
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> answer your cry.May the name of the God of
        Jacob keep you safe from all harm.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May he send you help from his sanctuaryand strengthen you from Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'May he remember all your giftsand look favorably on your burnt offerings.
        Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "May he grant your heart\u2019s desiresand make all your plans succeed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May we shout for joy when we hear of your victoryand raise a victory
        banner in the name of our God.May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> answer
        all your prayers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now I know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rescues his anointed
        king.He will answer him from his holy heavenand rescue him by his great power.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some nations boast of their chariots and horses,but we boast in the
        name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those nations will fall down and collapse,but we will rise up and
        stand firm.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of David.  How the king rejoices
        in your strength, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!He shouts with joy because
        you give him victory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For you have given him his heart\u2019s desire;you have withheld
        nothing he requested. Interlude  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You welcomed him back with success and prosperity.You placed a crown
        of finest gold on his head.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He asked you to preserve his life,and you granted his request.The
        days of his life stretch on forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your victory brings him great honor,and you have clothed him with
        splendor and majesty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have endowed him with eternal blessingsand given him the joy
        of your presence.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the king trusts in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.The unfailing
        love of the Most High will keep him from stumbling.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will capture all your enemies.Your strong right hand will seize
        all who hate you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will throw them in a flaming furnacewhen you appear.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will consume them in his anger;fire will devour them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will wipe their children from the face of the earth;they will
        never have descendants.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Although they plot against you,their evil schemes will never succeed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For they will turn and runwhen they see your arrows aimed at them.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm of David, to be sung to the tune
        \u201CDoe of the Dawn.\u201D  My God, my God, why have you abandoned me?Why
        are you so far away when I groan for help?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Every day I call to you, my God, but you do not answer.Every night
        I lift my voice, but I find no relief.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet you are holy,enthroned on the praises of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our ancestors trusted in you,and you rescued them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They cried out to you and were saved.They trusted in you and were
        never disgraced.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I am a worm and not a man.I am scorned and despised by all!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Everyone who sees me mocks me.They sneer and shake their heads, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIs this the one who relies on the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?Then
        let the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> save him!If the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        loves him so much,let the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rescue him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet you brought me safely from my mother\u2019s womband led me to
        trust you at my mother\u2019s breast.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I was thrust into your arms at my birth.You have been my God from
        the moment I was born.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not stay so far from me,for trouble is near,and no one else can
        help me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My enemies surround me like a herd of bulls;fierce bulls of Bashan
        have hemmed me in!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Like lions they open their jaws against me,roaring and tearing into
        their prey.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My life is poured out like water,and all my bones are out of joint.My
        heart is like wax,melting within me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My strength has dried up like sunbaked clay.My tongue sticks to the
        roof of my mouth.You have laid me in the dust and left me for dead.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My enemies surround me like a pack of dogs;an evil gang closes in
        on me.They have pierced[[COMMENT(0)]] my hands and feet.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:16 '
        content: As in some Hebrew manuscripts and Greek and Syriac versions; most
          Hebrew manuscripts read <b>They are like a lion at.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I can count all my bones.My enemies stare at me and gloat.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They divide my garments among themselvesand throw dice[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for my clothing.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:18 '
        content: Hebrew <b>cast lots.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, do not stay far away!You are my strength;
        come quickly to my aid!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Save me from the sword;spare my precious life from these dogs.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Snatch me from the lion\u2019s jawsand from the horns of these wild
        oxen.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will proclaim your name to my brothers and sisters.[[COMMENT(0)]]I
        will praise you among your assembled people.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:22 '
        content: Hebrew <b>my brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, all you who fear him!Honor
        him, all you descendants of Jacob!Show him reverence, all you descendants
        of Israel!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he has not ignored or belittled the suffering of the needy.He
        has not turned his back on them,but has listened to their cries for help.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will praise you in the great assembly.I will fulfill my vows in
        the presence of those who worship you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The poor will eat and be satisfied.All who seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will praise him.Their hearts will rejoice with everlasting joy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The whole earth will acknowledge the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and return to him.All the families of the nations will bow down before him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For royal power belongs to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.He rules
        all the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the rich of the earth feast and worship.Bow before him, all who
        are mortal,all whose lives will end as dust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our children will also serve him.Future generations will hear about
        the wonders of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm of David.  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is my shepherd;I
        have all that I need.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He lets me rest in green meadows;he leads me beside peaceful streams.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He renews my strength.He guides me along right paths,bringing honor
        to his name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even when I walkthrough the darkest valley,[[COMMENT(0)]]I will not
        be afraid,for you are close beside me.Your rod and your staffprotect and
        comfort me.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:4 '
        content: Or <b>the dark valley of death.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'You prepare a feast for mein the presence of my enemies.You honor
        me by anointing my head with oil.My cup overflows with blessings.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "A psalm of David.  The earth is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s,
        and everything in it.The world and all its people belong to him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For he laid the earth\u2019s foundation on the seasand built it on
        the ocean depths.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who may climb the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?Who
        may stand in his holy place?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Only those whose hands and hearts are pure,who do not worship idolsand
        never tell lies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will receive the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s blessingand
        have a right relationship with God their savior.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Such people may seek youand worship in your presence, O God of Jacob.[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        Interlude  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:6 '
        content: As in two Hebrew manuscripts and Greek and Syriac versions; most
          Hebrew manuscripts read <b>O Jacob.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Open up, ancient gates!Open up, ancient doors,and let the King of
        glory enter.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who is the King of glory?The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, strong
        and mighty;the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, invincible in battle.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Open up, ancient gates!Open up, ancient doors,and let the King of
        glory enter.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]]A psalm of David.  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        I give my life to you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '25 '
        content: '  This psalm is a Hebrew acrostic poem; each verse begins with
          a successive letter of the Hebrew alphabet.  '
    - title: 
      content: 'I trust in you, my God!Do not let me be disgraced,or let my enemies
        rejoice in my defeat.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No one who trusts in you will ever be disgraced,but disgrace comes
        to those who try to deceive others.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Show me the right path, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;point out the
        road for me to follow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lead me by your truth and teach me,for you are the God who saves
        me.All day long I put my hope in you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, your compassion and unfailing
        love,which you have shown from long ages past.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not remember the rebellious sins of my youth.Remember me in the
        light of your unfailing love,for you are merciful, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is good and does what is right;he
        shows the proper path to those who go astray.  '
      comments: []
