  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "A psalm of David.  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is my light and
        my salvation\u2014so why should I be afraid?The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is my fortress, protecting me from danger,so why should I tremble?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When evil people come to devour me,when my enemies and foes attack
        me,they will stumble and fall.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though a mighty army surrounds me,my heart will not be afraid.Even
        if I am attacked,I will remain confident.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The one thing I ask of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014the thing
        I seek most\u2014is to live in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        all the days of my life,delighting in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        perfectionsand meditating in his Temple.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he will conceal me there when troubles come;he will hide me in
        his sanctuary.He will place me out of reach on a high rock.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I will hold my head highabove my enemies who surround me.At
