      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wake up, O Lord! Why do you sleep?Get up! Do not reject us forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why do you look the other way?Why do you ignore our suffering and
        oppression?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We collapse in the dust,lying face down in the dirt.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A love song to be sung to the tune \u201CLilies.\u201D
        A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of the descendants of Korah.  Beautiful words stir
        my heart.I will recite a lovely poem about the king,for my tongue is like
        the pen of a skillful poet.  "
      comments:
      - number: '45:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>maskil. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: 'You are the most handsome of all.Gracious words stream from your
        lips.God himself has blessed you forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Put on your sword, O mighty warrior!You are so glorious, so majestic!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In your majesty, ride out to victory,defending truth, humility, and
        justice.Go forth to perform awe-inspiring deeds!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your arrows are sharp, piercing your enemies\u2019 hearts.The nations
        fall beneath your feet.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your throne, O God,[[COMMENT(0)]] endures forever and ever.You rule
        with a scepter of justice.  '
      comments:
      - number: '45:6 '
        content: Or <b>Your divine throne.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'You love justice and hate evil.Therefore God, your God, has anointed
        you,pouring out the oil of joy on you more than on anyone else.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Myrrh, aloes, and cassia perfume your robes.In ivory palaces the
        music of strings entertains you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Kings\u2019 daughters are among your noble women.At your right side
        stands the queen,wearing jewelry of finest gold from Ophir!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen to me, O royal daughter; take to heart what I say.Forget your
        people and your family far away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For your royal husband delights in your beauty;honor him, for he
        is your lord.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The princess of Tyre[[COMMENT(0)]] will shower you with gifts.The
        wealthy will beg your favor.  '
      comments:
      - number: '45:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>The daughter of Tyre.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The bride, a princess, looks gloriousin her golden gown.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In her beautiful robes, she is led to the king,accompanied by her
        bridesmaids.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What a joyful and enthusiastic processionas they enter the king\u2019s
        palace!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your sons will become kings like their father.You will make them
        rulers over many lands.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A song of the descendants of Korah, to be
        sung by soprano voices.[[COMMENT(0)]]  God is our refuge and strength,always
        ready to help in times of trouble.  '
      comments:
      - number: '46:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>according to alamoth.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'So we will not fear when earthquakes comeand the mountains crumble
        into the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the oceans roar and foam.Let the mountains tremble as the waters
        surge! Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A river brings joy to the city of our God,the sacred home of the
        Most High.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God dwells in that city; it cannot be destroyed.From the very break
        of day, God will protect it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The nations are in chaos,and their kingdoms crumble!God\u2019s voice
        thunders,and the earth melts!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies is here among
        us;the God of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] is our fortress. Interlude  "
      comments:
      - number: '46:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Jacob; </b>also in 46:11. See note on 44:4.
    - title: 
      content: 'Come, see the glorious works of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:See
        how he brings destruction upon the world.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He causes wars to end throughout the earth.He breaks the bow and
        snaps the spear;he burns the shields with fire.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBe still, and know that I am God!I will be honored by every
        nation.I will be honored throughout the world.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of the descendants of Korah.  Come,
        everyone! Clap your hands!Shout to God with joyful praise!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> Most High is awesome.He is the
        great King of all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He subdues the nations before us,putting our enemies beneath our
        feet.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He chose the Promised Land as our inheritance,the proud possession
        of Jacob\u2019s descendants, whom he loves. Interlude  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God has ascended with a mighty shout.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has ascended with trumpets blaring.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sing praises to God, sing praises;sing praises to our King, sing
        praises!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God is the King over all the earth.Praise him with a psalm.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '47:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>maskil. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: 'God reigns above the nations,sitting on his holy throne.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song. A psalm of the descendants of Korah.  How great is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,how
        deserving of praise,in the city of our God,which sits on his holy mountain!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is high and magnificent;the whole earth rejoices to see it!Mount
        Zion, the holy mountain,[[COMMENT(0)]]is the city of the great King!  '
      comments:
      - number: '48:2 '
        content: Or <b>Mount Zion, in the far north; </b>Hebrew reads <b>Mount Zion,
          the heights of Zaphon.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "God himself is in Jerusalem\u2019s towers,revealing himself as its
        defender.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The kings of the earth joined forcesand advanced against the city.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But when they saw it, they were stunned;they were terrified and ran
        away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were gripped with terrorand writhed in pain like a woman in
        labor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You destroyed them like the mighty ships of Tarshishshattered by
        a powerful east wind.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We had heard of the city\u2019s glory,but now we have seen it ourselves\u2014the
        city of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.It is the
        city of our God;he will make it safe forever. Interlude  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O God, we meditate on your unfailing loveas we worship in your Temple.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As your name deserves, O God,you will be praised to the ends of the
        earth.Your strong right hand is filled with victory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the people on Mount Zion rejoice.Let all the towns of Judah be
        gladbecause of your justice.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Go, inspect the city of Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]Walk around and count
        the many towers.  '
      comments:
      - number: '48:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Take note of the fortified walls,and tour all the citadels,that you
        may describe themto future generations.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of the descendants of Korah.  Listen
        to this, all you people!Pay attention, everyone in the world!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "High and low,rich and poor\u2014listen!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For my words are wise,and my thoughts are filled with insight.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I listen carefully to many proverbsand solve riddles with inspiration
        from a harp.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why should I fear when trouble comes,when enemies surround me?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They trust in their wealthand boast of great riches.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet they cannot redeem themselves from death[[COMMENT(0)]]by paying
        a ransom to God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '49:7 '
        content: Some Hebrew manuscripts read <b>no one can redeem the life of another.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Redemption does not come so easily,for no one can ever pay enough  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'to live foreverand never see the grave.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who are wise must finally die,just like the foolish and senseless,leaving
        all their wealth behind.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The grave[[COMMENT(0)]] is their eternal home,where they will stay
        forever.They may name their estates after themselves,  '
      comments:
      - number: '49:11 '
        content: As in Greek and Syriac versions; Hebrew reads <b>Their inward [thought].</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'but their fame will not last.They will die, just like animals.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is the fate of fools,though they are remembered as being wise.[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        Interlude  '
      comments:
      - number: '49:13 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'Like sheep, they are led to the grave,[[COMMENT(0)]]where death will
        be their shepherd.In the morning the godly will rule over them.Their bodies
        will rot in the grave,far from their grand estates.  '
      comments:
      - number: '49:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Sheol; </b>also in 49:14b, 15.
    - title: 
      content: 'But as for me, God will redeem my life.He will snatch me from the
        power of the grave. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So don\u2019t be dismayed when the wicked grow richand their homes
        become ever more splendid.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For when they die, they take nothing with them.Their wealth will
        not follow them into the grave.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In this life they consider themselves fortunateand are applauded
        for their success.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But they will die like all before themand never again see the light
        of day.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm of Asaph.  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the Mighty One,
        is God,and he has spoken;he has summoned all humanityfrom where the sun rises
        to where it sets.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'From Mount Zion, the perfection of beauty,God shines in glorious
        radiance.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our God approaches,and he is not silent.Fire devours everything in
        his way,and a great storm rages around him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He calls on the heavens above and earth belowto witness the judgment
        of his people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBring my faithful people to me\u2014those who made a covenant
        with me by giving sacrifices.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then let the heavens proclaim his justice,for God himself will be
        the judge. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO my people, listen as I speak.Here are my charges against
        you, O Israel:I am God, your God!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have no complaint about your sacrificesor the burnt offerings you
        constantly offer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I do not need the bulls from your barnsor the goats from your
        pens.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For all the animals of the forest are mine,and I own the cattle on
        a thousand hills.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I know every bird on the mountains,and all the animals of the field
        are mine.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If I were hungry, I would not tell you,for all the world is mine
        and everything in it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do I eat the meat of bulls?Do I drink the blood of goats?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Make thankfulness your sacrifice to God,and keep the vows you made
        to the Most High.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then call on me when you are in trouble,and I will rescue you,and
        you will give me glory.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But God says to the wicked:\u201CWhy bother reciting my decreesand
        pretending to obey my covenant?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For you refuse my disciplineand treat my words like trash.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you see thieves, you approve of them,and you spend your time
        with adulterers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your mouth is filled with wickedness,and your tongue is full of lies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You sit around and slander your brother\u2014your own mother\u2019s
        son.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "While you did all this, I remained silent,and you thought I didn\u2019t
        care.But now I will rebuke you,listing all my charges against you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Repent, all of you who forget me,or I will tear you apart,and no
        one will help you.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of David, regarding the time Nathan
        the prophet came to him after David had committed adultery with Bathsheba. 
        Have mercy on me, O God,because of your unfailing love.Because of your great
        compassion,blot out the stain of my sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wash me clean from my guilt.Purify me from my sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I recognize my rebellion;it haunts me day and night.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Against you, and you alone, have I sinned;I have done what is evil
        in your sight.You will be proved right in what you say,and your judgment
        against me is just.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '51:4 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>and you will win your case in court. </b>Compare
          Rom 3:4.
    - title: 
      content: "For I was born a sinner\u2014yes, from the moment my mother conceived
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you desire honesty from the womb,[[COMMENT(0)]]teaching me wisdom
        even there.  '
      comments:
      - number: '51:6 '
        content: Or <b>from the heart; </b>Hebrew reads <b>in the inward parts.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Purify me from my sins,[[COMMENT(0)]] and I will be clean;wash me,
        and I will be whiter than snow.  '
      comments:
      - number: '51:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Purify me with the hyssop branch.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, give me back my joy again;you have broken me\u2014now let me
        rejoice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t keep looking at my sins.Remove the stain of my guilt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Create in me a clean heart, O God.Renew a loyal spirit within me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do not banish me from your presence,and don\u2019t take your Holy
        Spirit[[COMMENT(0)]] from me.  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:11 '
        content: Or <b>your spirit of holiness.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Restore to me the joy of your salvation,and make me willing to obey
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I will teach your ways to rebels,and they will return to you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Forgive me for shedding blood, O God who saves;then I will joyfully
        sing of your forgiveness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Unseal my lips, O Lord,that my mouth may praise you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You do not desire a sacrifice, or I would offer one.You do not want
        a burnt offering.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The sacrifice you desire is a broken spirit.You will not reject a
        broken and repentant heart, O God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look with favor on Zion and help her;rebuild the walls of Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of David, regarding
        the time Doeg the Edomite said to Saul, \u201CDavid has gone to see Ahimelech.\u201D 
        Why do you boast about your crimes, great warrior?Don\u2019t you realize
        God\u2019s justice continues forever?  "
      comments:
      - number: '52:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>maskil. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: "All day long you plot destruction.Your tongue cuts like a sharp razor;you\u2019re
        an expert at telling lies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You love evil more than goodand lies more than truth. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You love to destroy others with your words,you liar!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But God will strike you down once and for all.He will pull you from
        your homeand uproot you from the land of the living. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The righteous will see it and be amazed.They will laugh and say,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook what happens to mighty warriorswho do not trust in God.They
        trust their wealth insteadand grow more and more bold in their wickedness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I am like an olive tree, thriving in the house of God.I will
        always trust in God\u2019s unfailing love.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A meditation; a psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of David. 
        Only fools say in their hearts,\u201CThere is no God.\u201DThey are corrupt,
        and their actions are evil;not one of them does good!  "
      comments:
      - number: '53:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>According to mahalath; a maskil. </b>These may be literary
          or musical terms.
    - title: 
      content: 'God looks down from heavenon the entire human race;he looks to see
        if anyone is truly wise,if anyone seeks God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But no, all have turned away;all have become corrupt.[[COMMENT(0)]]No
        one does good,not a single one!  '
      comments:
      - number: '53:3 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>have become useless. </b>Compare Rom 3:12.
    - title: 
      content: "Will those who do evil never learn?They eat up my people like breadand
        wouldn\u2019t think of praying to God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Terror will grip them,terror like they have never known before.God
        will scatter the bones of your enemies.You will put them to shame, for God
        has rejected them.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of David, regarding
        the time the Ziphites came and said to Saul, \u201CWe know where David is
        hiding.\u201D To be accompanied by stringed instruments.  Come with great
        power, O God, and rescue me!Defend me with your might.  "
      comments:
      - number: '54:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>maskil. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen to my prayer, O God.Pay attention to my plea.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For strangers are attacking me;violent people are trying to kill
        me.They care nothing for God. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But God is my helper.The Lord keeps me alive!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May the evil plans of my enemies be turned against them.Do as you
        promised and put an end to them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will sacrifice a voluntary offering to you;I will praise your name,
        O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,for it is good.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of David, to be accompanied
        by stringed instruments.  Listen to my prayer, O God.Do not ignore my cry
        for help!  '
      comments:
      - number: '55:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>maskil. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: 'Please listen and answer me,for I am overwhelmed by my troubles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My enemies shout at me,making loud and wicked threats.They bring
        trouble on meand angrily hunt me down.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My heart pounds in my chest.The terror of death assaults me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Fear and trembling overwhelm me,and I can\u2019t stop shaking.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Oh, that I had wings like a dove;then I would fly away and rest!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I would fly far awayto the quiet of the wilderness. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How quickly I would escape\u2014far from this wild storm of hatred.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Confuse them, Lord, and frustrate their plans,for I see violence
        and conflict in the city.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Its walls are patrolled day and night against invaders,but the real
        danger is wickedness within the city.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Everything is falling apart;threats and cheating are rampant in the
        streets.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is not an enemy who taunts me\u2014I could bear that.It is not
        my foes who so arrogantly insult me\u2014I could have hidden from them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Instead, it is you\u2014my equal,my companion and close friend.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What good fellowship we once enjoyedas we walked together to the
        house of God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let death stalk my enemies;let the grave[[COMMENT(0)]] swallow them
        alive,for evil makes its home within them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '55:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>let Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But I will call on God,and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will rescue
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Morning, noon, and nightI cry out in my distress,and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        hears my voice.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He ransoms me and keeps me safefrom the battle waged against me,though
        many still oppose me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God, who has ruled forever,will hear me and humble them. InterludeFor
        my enemies refuse to change their ways;they do not fear God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As for my companion, he betrayed his friends;he broke his promises.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His words are as smooth as butter,but in his heart is war.His words
        are as soothing as lotion,but underneath are daggers!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give your burdens to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and he will
        take care of you.He will not permit the godly to slip and fall.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of David, regarding
        the time the Philistines seized him in Gath. To be sung to the tune \u201CDove
        on Distant Oaks.\u201D  O God, have mercy on me,for people are hounding me.My
        foes attack me all day long.  "
      comments:
      - number: '56:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>miktam. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: 'I am constantly hounded by those who slander me,and many are boldly
        attacking me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But when I am afraid,I will put my trust in you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I praise God for what he has promised.I trust in God, so why should
        I be afraid?What can mere mortals do to me?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are always twisting what I say;they spend their days plotting
        to harm me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They come together to spy on me\u2014watching my every step, eager
        to kill me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let them get away with their wickedness;in your anger,
        O God, bring them down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You keep track of all my sorrows.[[COMMENT(0)]]You have collected
        all my tears in your bottle.You have recorded each one in your book.  '
      comments:
      - number: '56:8 '
        content: Or <b>my wanderings.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'My enemies will retreat when I call to you for help.This I know:
        God is on my side!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I praise God for what he has promised;yes, I praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        for what he has promised.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I trust in God, so why should I be afraid?What can mere mortals do
        to me?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will fulfill my vows to you, O God,and will offer a sacrifice of
        thanks for your help.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of David, regarding
        the time he fled from Saul and went into the cave. To be sung to the tune
        \u201CDo Not Destroy!\u201D  Have mercy on me, O God, have mercy!I look to
        you for protection.I will hide beneath the shadow of your wingsuntil the
        danger passes by.  "
      comments:
      - number: '57:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>miktam. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: 'I cry out to God Most High,[[COMMENT(0)]]to God who will fulfill
        his purpose for me.  '
      comments:
      - number: '57:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Elohim-Elyon.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'He will send help from heaven to rescue me,disgracing those who hound
        me. InterludeMy God will send forth his unfailing love and faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am surrounded by fierce lionswho greedily devour human prey\u2014whose
        teeth pierce like spears and arrows,and whose tongues cut like swords.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Be exalted, O God, above the highest heavens!May your glory shine
        over all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My enemies have set a trap for me.I am weary from distress.They have
        dug a deep pit in my path,but they themselves have fallen into it. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My heart is confident in you, O God;my heart is confident.No wonder
        I can sing your praises!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wake up, my heart!Wake up, O lyre and harp!I will wake the dawn with
        my song.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will thank you, Lord, among all the people.I will sing your praises
        among the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For your unfailing love is as high as the heavens.Your faithfulness
        reaches to the clouds.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of David, to be sung
        to the tune \u201CDo Not Destroy!\u201D  Justice\u2014do you rulers[[COMMENT(1)]]
        know the meaning of the word?Do you judge the people fairly?  "
      comments:
      - number: '58:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>miktam. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
      - number: '58:1 '
        content: Or <b>you gods.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'No! You plot injustice in your hearts.You spread violence throughout
        the land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These wicked people are born sinners;even from birth they have lied
        and gone their own way.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They spit venom like deadly snakes;they are like cobras that refuse
        to listen,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'ignoring the tunes of the snake charmers,no matter how skillfully
        they play.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Break off their fangs, O God!Smash the jaws of these lions, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May they disappear like water into thirsty ground.Make their weapons
        useless in their hands.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '58:7 '
        content: Or <b>Let them be trodden down and wither like grass. </b>The meaning
          of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'May they be like snails that dissolve into slime,like a stillborn
        child who will never see the sun.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God will sweep them away, both young and old,faster than a pot heats
        over burning thorns.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godly will rejoice when they see injustice avenged.They will
        wash their feet in the blood of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of David, regarding
        the time Saul sent soldiers to watch David\u2019s house in order to kill
        him. To be sung to the tune \u201CDo Not Destroy!\u201D  Rescue me from my
        enemies, O God.Protect me from those who have come to destroy me.  "
      comments:
      - number: '59:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>miktam. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: 'Rescue me from these criminals;save me from these murderers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have set an ambush for me.Fierce enemies are out there waiting,
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,though I have not sinned or offended them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have done nothing wrong,yet they prepare to attack me.Wake up!
        See what is happening and help me!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God
        of Israel,wake up and punish those hostile nations.Show no mercy to wicked
        traitors. Interlude  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They come out at night,snarling like vicious dogsas they prowl the
        streets.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to the filth that comes from their mouths;their words cut
        like swords.\u201CAfter all, who can hear us?\u201D they sneer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you laugh at them.You scoff at all
        the hostile nations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You are my strength; I wait for you to rescue me,for you, O God,
        are my fortress.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In his unfailing love, my God will stand with me.He will let me look
        down in triumph on all my enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t kill them, for my people soon forget such lessons;stagger
        them with your power, and bring them to their knees,O Lord our shield.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because of the sinful things they say,because of the evil that is
        on their lips,let them be captured by their pride,their curses, and their
        lies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Destroy them in your anger!Wipe them out completely!Then the whole
        world will knowthat God reigns in Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  Interlude  '
      comments:
      - number: '59:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Jacob. </b>See note on 44:4.
    - title: 
      content: 'My enemies come out at night,snarling like vicious dogsas they prowl
        the streets.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They scavenge for foodbut go to sleep unsatisfied.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '59:15 '
        content: "Or <b>and growl if they don\u2019t get enough.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'But as for me, I will sing about your power.Each morning I will sing
        with joy about your unfailing love.For you have been my refuge,a place of
        safety when I am in distress.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of David useful for
        teaching, regarding the time David fought Aram-naharaim and Aram-zobah, and
        Joab returned and killed 12,000 Edomites in the Valley of Salt. To be sung
        to the tune \u201CLily of the Testimony.\u201D  You have rejected us, O God,
        and broken our defenses.You have been angry with us; now restore us to your
        favor.  "
      comments:
      - number: '60:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>miktam. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: 'You have shaken our land and split it open.Seal the cracks, for the
        land trembles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have been very hard on us,making us drink wine that sent us reeling.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you have raised a banner for those who fear you\u2014a rallying
        point in the face of attack. Interlude  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now rescue your beloved people.Answer and save us by your power.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God has promised this by his holiness[[COMMENT(0)]]:\u201CI will
        divide up Shechem with joy.I will measure out the valley of Succoth.  "
      comments:
      - number: '60:6 '
        content: Or <b>in his sanctuary.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Gilead is mine,and Manasseh, too.Ephraim, my helmet, will produce
        my warriors,and Judah, my scepter, will produce my kings.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Moab, my washbasin, will become my servant,and I will wipe my
        feet on Edomand shout in triumph over Philistia.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who will bring me into the fortified city?Who will bring me victory
        over Edom?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Have you rejected us, O God?Will you no longer march with our armies?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Oh, please help us against our enemies,for all human help is useless.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of David, to be accompanied by stringed
        instruments.  O God, listen to my cry!Hear my prayer!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'From the ends of the earth,I cry to you for helpwhen my heart is
        overwhelmed.Lead me to the towering rock of safety,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for you are my safe refuge,a fortress where my enemies cannot reach
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let me live forever in your sanctuary,safe beneath the shelter of
        your wings! Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For you have heard my vows, O God.You have given me an inheritance
        reserved for those who fear your name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Add many years to the life of the king!May his years span the generations!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "May he reign under God\u2019s protection forever.May your unfailing
        love and faithfulness watch over him.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For Jeduthun, the choir director: A psalm of David.  I wait quietly
        before God,for my victory comes from him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He alone is my rock and my salvation,my fortress where I will never
        be shaken.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So many enemies against one man\u2014all of them trying to kill me.To
        them I\u2019m just a broken-down wallor a tottering fence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They plan to topple me from my high position.They delight in telling
        lies about me.They praise me to my facebut curse me in their hearts. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let all that I am wait quietly before God,for my hope is in him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He alone is my rock and my salvation,my fortress where I will not
        be shaken.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My victory and honor come from God alone.He is my refuge, a rock
        where no enemy can reach me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O my people, trust in him at all times.Pour out your heart to him,for
        God is our refuge. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Common people are as worthless as a puff of wind,and the powerful
        are not what they appear to be.If you weigh them on the scales,together they
        are lighter than a breath of air.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t make your living by extortionor put your hope in stealing.And
        if your wealth increases,don\u2019t make it the center of your life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God has spoken plainly,and I have heard it many times:Power, O God,
        belongs to you;  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm of David, regarding a time when David was in the wilderness
        of Judah.  O God, you are my God;I earnestly search for you.My soul thirsts
        for you;my whole body longs for youin this parched and weary landwhere there
        is no water.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have seen you in your sanctuaryand gazed upon your power and glory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your unfailing love is better than life itself;how I praise you!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will praise you as long as I live,lifting up my hands to you in
        prayer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You satisfy me more than the richest feast.I will praise you with
        songs of joy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I lie awake thinking of you,meditating on you through the night.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because you are my helper,I sing for joy in the shadow of your wings.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I cling to you;your strong right hand holds me securely.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But those plotting to destroy me will come to ruin.They will go down
        into the depths of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will die by the swordand become the food of jackals.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm of David.  O God, listen to my complaint.Protect
        my life from my enemies\u2019 threats.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Hide me from the plots of this evil mob,from this gang of wrongdoers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They sharpen their tongues like swordsand aim their bitter words
        like arrows.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They shoot from ambush at the innocent,attacking suddenly and fearlessly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They encourage each other to do eviland plan how to set their traps
        in secret.\u201CWho will ever notice?\u201D they ask.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As they plot their crimes, they say,\u201CWe have devised the perfect
        plan!\u201DYes, the human heart and mind are cunning.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But God himself will shoot them with his arrows,suddenly striking
        them down.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their own tongues will ruin them,and all who see them will shake
        their heads in scorn.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then everyone will be afraid;they will proclaim the mighty acts of
        Godand realize all the amazing things he does.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A song. A psalm of David.  What mighty praise,
        O God,belongs to you in Zion.We will fulfill our vows to you,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for you answer our prayers.All of us must come to you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though we are overwhelmed by our sins,you forgive them all.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What joy for those you choose to bring near,those who live in your
        holy courts.What festivities await usinside your holy Temple.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You faithfully answer our prayers with awesome deeds,O God our savior.You
        are the hope of everyone on earth,even those who sail on distant seas.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You formed the mountains by your powerand armed yourself with mighty
        strength.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You quieted the raging oceanswith their pounding wavesand silenced
        the shouting of the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who live at the ends of the earthstand in awe of your wonders.From
        where the sun rises to where it sets,you inspire shouts of joy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You take care of the earth and water it,making it rich and fertile.The
        river of God has plenty of water;it provides a bountiful harvest of grain,for
        you have ordered it so.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You drench the plowed ground with rain,melting the clods and leveling
        the ridges.You soften the earth with showersand bless its abundant crops.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You crown the year with a bountiful harvest;even the hard pathways
        overflow with abundance.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The grasslands of the wilderness become a lush pasture,and the hillsides
        blossom with joy.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A song. A psalm.  Shout joyful praises to
        God, all the earth!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sing about the glory of his name!Tell the world how glorious he is.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Say to God, \u201CHow awesome are your deeds!Your enemies cringe
        before your mighty power.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Everything on earth will worship you;they will sing your praises,shouting
        your name in glorious songs.\u201D Interlude  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Come and see what our God has done,what awesome miracles he performs
        for people!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He made a dry path through the Red Sea,[[COMMENT(0)]]and his people
        went across on foot.There we rejoiced in him.  '
      comments:
      - number: '66:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the sea.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For by his great power he rules forever.He watches every movement
        of the nations;let no rebel rise in defiance. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the whole world bless our Godand loudly sing his praises.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our lives are in his hands,and he keeps our feet from stumbling.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have tested us, O God;you have purified us like silver.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You captured us in your netand laid the burden of slavery on our
        backs.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you put a leader over us.[[COMMENT(0)]]We went through fire
        and flood,but you brought us to a place of great abundance.  '
      comments:
      - number: '66:12 '
        content: Or <b>You made people ride over our heads.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Now I come to your Temple with burnt offeringsto fulfill the vows
        I made to you\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'yes, the sacred vows that I madewhen I was in deep trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why I am sacrificing burnt offerings to you\u2014the best
        of my rams as a pleasing aroma,and a sacrifice of bulls and male goats. Interlude  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Come and listen, all you who fear God,and I will tell you what he
        did for me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I cried out to him for help,praising him as I spoke.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If I had not confessed the sin in my heart,the Lord would not have
        listened.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But God did listen!He paid attention to my prayer.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A song. A psalm, to be accompanied by stringed
        instruments.  May God be merciful and bless us.May his face smile with favor
        on us. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May your ways be known throughout the earth,your saving power among
        people everywhere.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May the nations praise you, O God.Yes, may all the nations praise
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the whole world sing for joy,because you govern the nations with
        justiceand guide the people of the whole world. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May the nations praise you, O God.Yes, may all the nations praise
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the earth will yield its harvests,and God, our God, will richly
        bless us.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A song. A psalm of David.  Rise up, O God,
        and scatter your enemies.Let those who hate God run for their lives.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Blow them away like smoke.Melt them like wax in a fire.Let the wicked
        perish in the presence of God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But let the godly rejoice.Let them be glad in God\u2019s presence.Let
        them be filled with joy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Sing praises to God and to his name!Sing loud praises to him who
        rides the clouds.[[COMMENT(0)]]His name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014rejoice
        in his presence!  "
      comments:
      - number: '68:4 '
        content: Or <b>rides through the deserts.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Father to the fatherless, defender of widows\u2014this is God, whose
        dwelling is holy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God places the lonely in families;he sets the prisoners free and
        gives them joy.But he makes the rebellious live in a sun-scorched land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O God, when you led your people out from Egypt,when you marched through
        the dry wasteland, Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the earth trembled, and the heavens poured down rainbefore you, the
        God of Sinai,before God, the God of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You sent abundant rain, O God,to refresh the weary land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There your people finally settled,and with a bountiful harvest, O
        God,you provided for your needy people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Lord gives the word,and a great army[[COMMENT(0)]] brings the
        good news.  '
      comments:
      - number: '68:11 '
        content: Or <b>a host of women.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Enemy kings and their armies flee,while the women of Israel divide
        the plunder.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even those who lived among the sheepfolds found treasures\u2014doves
        with wings of silverand feathers of gold.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Almighty scattered the enemy kingslike a blowing snowstorm on
        Mount Zalmon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The mountains of Bashan are majestic,with many peaks stretching high
        into the sky.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why do you look with envy, O rugged mountains,at Mount Zion, where
        God has chosen to live,where the <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>himself will
        live forever?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Surrounded by unnumbered thousands of chariots,the Lord came from
        Mount Sinai into his sanctuary.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you ascended to the heights,you led a crowd of captives.You
        received gifts from the people,even from those who rebelled against you.Now
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God will live among us there.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Praise the Lord; praise God our savior!For each day he carries us
        in his arms. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our God is a God who saves!The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        rescues us from death.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But God will smash the heads of his enemies,crushing the skulls of
        those who love their guilty ways.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Lord says, \u201CI will bring my enemies down from Bashan;I will
        bring them up from the depths of the sea.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You, my people, will wash[[COMMENT(0)]] your feet in their blood,and
        even your dogs will get their share!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '68:23 '
        content: As in Greek and Syriac versions; Hebrew reads <b>shatter.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Your procession has come into view, O God\u2014the procession of
        my God and King as he goes into the sanctuary.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Singers are in front, musicians behind;between them are young women
        playing tambourines.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Praise God, all you people of Israel;praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the source of Israel\u2019s life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
