      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm of David, to be sung to the tune
        \u201CLilies.\u201D  Save me, O God,for the floodwaters are up to my neck.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Deeper and deeper I sink into the mire;I can\u2019t find a foothold.I
        am in deep water,and the floods overwhelm me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am exhausted from crying for help;my throat is parched.My eyes
        are swollen with weeping,waiting for my God to help me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who hate me without causeoutnumber the hairs on my head.Many
        enemies try to destroy me with lies,demanding that I give back what I didn\u2019t
        steal.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O God, you know how foolish I am;my sins cannot be hidden from you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let those who trust in you be ashamed because of me,O
        Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.Don\u2019t
        let me cause them to be humiliated,O God of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I endure insults for your sake;humiliation is written all over
        my face.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even my own brothers pretend they don\u2019t know me;they treat me
        like a stranger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Passion for your house has consumed me,and the insults of those who
        insult you have fallen on me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When I weep and fast,they scoff at me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When I dress in burlap to show sorrow,they make fun of me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am the favorite topic of town gossip,and all the drunks sing about
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I keep praying to you, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,hoping this
        time you will show me favor.In your unfailing love, O God,answer my prayer
        with your sure salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Rescue me from the mud;don\u2019t let me sink any deeper!Save me
        from those who hate me,and pull me from these deep waters.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let the floods overwhelm me,or the deep waters swallow
        me,or the pit of death devour me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Answer my prayers, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,for your unfailing
        love is wonderful.Take care of me,for your mercy is so plentiful.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t hide from your servant;answer me quickly, for I am in
        deep trouble!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Come and redeem me;free me from my enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You know of my shame, scorn, and disgrace.You see all that my enemies
        are doing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their insults have broken my heart,and I am in despair.If only one
        person would show some pity;if only one would turn and comfort me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But instead, they give me poison[[COMMENT(0)]] for food;they offer
        me sour wine for my thirst.  '
      comments:
      - number: '69:21 '
        content: Or <b>gall.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the bountiful table set before them become a snareand their prosperity
        become a trap.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '69:22 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>Let their bountiful table set before them
