      comments:
      - number: '69:23 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>and let their backs be bent forever. </b>Compare
          Rom 11:10.
    - title: 
      content: 'Pour out your fury on them;consume them with your burning anger.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let their homes become desolateand their tents be deserted.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'To the one you have punished, they add insult to injury;they add
        to the pain of those you have hurt.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Pile their sins up high,and don\u2019t let them go free.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Erase their names from the Book of Life;don\u2019t let them be counted
        among the righteous.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am suffering and in pain.Rescue me, O God, by your saving power.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I will praise God\u2019s name with singing,and I will honor
        him with thanksgiving.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For this will please the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> more than sacrificing
        cattle,more than presenting a bull with its horns and hooves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The humble will see their God at work and be glad.Let all who seek
        God\u2019s help be encouraged.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> hears the cries of the needy;he
        does not despise his imprisoned people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Praise him, O heaven and earth,the seas and all that move in them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God will save Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]and rebuild the towns of
        Judah.His people will live thereand settle in their own land.  '
      comments:
      - number: '69:35 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of David, asking God to remember
        him.  Please, God, rescue me!Come quickly, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and
        help me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May those who try to kill mebe humiliated and put to shame.May those
        who take delight in my troublebe turned back in disgrace.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let them be horrified by their shame,for they said, \u201CAha! We\u2019ve
        got him now!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But may all who search for yoube filled with joy and gladness in
        you.May those who love your salvationrepeatedly shout, \u201CGod is great!\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I have come to you for protection;don\u2019t
        let me be disgraced.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Save me and rescue me,for you do what is right.Turn your ear to listen
        to me,and set me free.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Be my rock of safetywhere I can always hide.Give the order to save
        me,for you are my rock and my fortress.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My God, rescue me from the power of the wicked,from the clutches
        of cruel oppressors.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O Lord, you alone are my hope.I\u2019ve trusted you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        from childhood.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, you have been with me from birth;from my mother\u2019s womb
        you have cared for me.No wonder I am always praising you!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My life is an example to many,because you have been my strength and
        protection.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That is why I can never stop praising you;I declare your glory all
        day long.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And now, in my old age, don\u2019t set me aside.Don\u2019t abandon
        me when my strength is failing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For my enemies are whispering against me.They are plotting together
        to kill me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They say, \u201CGod has abandoned him.Let\u2019s go and get him,for
        no one will help him now.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O God, don\u2019t stay away.My God, please hurry to help me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Bring disgrace and destruction on my accusers.Humiliate and shame
        those who want to harm me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I will keep on hoping for your help;I will praise you more and
        more.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will tell everyone about your righteousness.All day long I will
        proclaim your saving power,though I am not skilled with words.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '71:15 '
        content: Or <b>though I cannot count it.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I will praise your mighty deeds, O Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.I
        will tell everyone that you alone are just.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O God, you have taught me from my earliest childhood,and I constantly
        tell others about the wonderful things you do.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now that I am old and gray,do not abandon me, O God.Let me proclaim
        your power to this new generation,your mighty miracles to all who come after
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your righteousness, O God, reaches to the highest heavens.You have
        done such wonderful things.Who can compare with you, O God?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have allowed me to suffer much hardship,but you will restore
        me to life againand lift me up from the depths of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will restore me to even greater honorand comfort me once again.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I will praise you with music on the harp,because you are faithful
        to your promises, O my God.I will sing praises to you with a lyre,O Holy
        One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will shout for joy and sing your praises,for you have ransomed
        me.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "A psalm of Solomon.  Give your love of justice to the king, O God,and
        righteousness to the king\u2019s son.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Help him judge your people in the right way;let the poor always be
        treated fairly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May the mountains yield prosperity for all,and may the hills be fruitful.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Help him to defend the poor,to rescue the children of the needy,and
        to crush their oppressors.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May they fear you[[COMMENT(0)]] as long as the sun shines,as long
        as the moon remains in the sky.Yes, forever!  '
      comments:
      - number: '72:5 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>May they endure.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "May the king\u2019s rule be refreshing like spring rain on freshly
        cut grass,like the showers that water the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May all the godly flourish during his reign.May there be abundant
        prosperity until the moon is no more.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May he reign from sea to sea,and from the Euphrates River[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to the ends of the earth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '72:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the river.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Desert nomads will bow before him;his enemies will fall before him
        in the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The western kings of Tarshish and other distant landswill bring him
        tribute.The eastern kings of Sheba and Sebawill bring him gifts.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All kings will bow before him,and all nations will serve him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will rescue the poor when they cry to him;he will help the oppressed,
        who have no one to defend them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He feels pity for the weak and the needy,and he will rescue them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will redeem them from oppression and violence,for their lives
        are precious to him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Long live the king!May the gold of Sheba be given to him.May the
        people always pray for himand bless him all day long.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May there be abundant grain throughout the land,flourishing even
        on the hilltops.May the fruit trees flourish like the trees of Lebanon,and
        may the people thrive like grass in a field.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "May the king\u2019s name endure forever;may it continue as long as
        the sun shines.May all nations be blessed through himand bring him praise.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God, the God of Israel,who
        alone does such wonderful things.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Praise his glorious name forever!Let the whole earth be filled with
        his glory.Amen and amen!  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "  Book Three (Psalms 73\u201389)"
      content: 'A psalm of Asaph.  Truly God is good to Israel,to those whose hearts
        are pure.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But as for me, I almost lost my footing.My feet were slipping, and
        I was almost gone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I envied the proudwhen I saw them prosper despite their wickedness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They seem to live such painless lives;their bodies are so healthy
        and strong.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They don\u2019t have troubles like other people;they\u2019re not
        plagued with problems like everyone else.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They wear pride like a jeweled necklaceand clothe themselves with
        cruelty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These fat cats have everythingtheir hearts could ever wish for!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They scoff and speak only evil;in their pride they seek to crush
        others.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They boast against the very heavens,and their words strut throughout
        the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And so the people are dismayed and confused,drinking in all their
        words.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat does God know?\u201D they ask.\u201CDoes the Most High
        even know what\u2019s happening?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look at these wicked people\u2014enjoying a life of ease while their
        riches multiply.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Did I keep my heart pure for nothing?Did I keep myself innocent for
        no reason?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I get nothing but trouble all day long;every morning brings me pain.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If I had really spoken this way to others,I would have been a traitor
        to your people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I tried to understand why the wicked prosper.But what a difficult
        task it is!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I went into your sanctuary, O God,and I finally understood the
        destiny of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Truly, you put them on a slippery pathand send them sliding over
        the cliff to destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In an instant they are destroyed,completely swept away by terrors.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you arise, O Lord,you will laugh at their silly ideasas a person
        laughs at dreams in the morning.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I realized that my heart was bitter,and I was all torn up inside.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was so foolish and ignorant\u2014I must have seemed like a senseless
        animal to you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet I still belong to you;you hold my right hand.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You guide me with your counsel,leading me to a glorious destiny.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Whom have I in heaven but you?I desire you more than anything on
        earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My health may fail, and my spirit may grow weak,but God remains the
        strength of my heart;he is mine forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who desert him will perish,for you destroy those who abandon
        you.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of Asaph.  O God, why have you rejected us
        so long?Why is your anger so intense against the sheep of your own pasture?  '
      comments:
      - number: '74:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>maskil. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember that we are the people you chose long ago,the tribe you
        redeemed as your own special possession!And remember Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        your home here on earth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '74:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Mount Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Walk through the awful ruins of the city;see how the enemy has destroyed
        your sanctuary.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There your enemies shouted their victorious battle cries;there they
        set up their battle standards.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They swung their axeslike woodcutters in a forest.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'With axes and picks,they smashed the carved paneling.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They burned your sanctuary to the ground.They defiled the place that
        bears your name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then they thought, \u201CLet\u2019s destroy everything!\u201DSo they
        burned down all the places where God was worshiped.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We no longer see your miraculous signs.All the prophets are gone,and
        no one can tell us when it will end.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How long, O God, will you allow our enemies to insult you?Will you
        let them dishonor your name forever?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why do you hold back your strong right hand?Unleash your powerful
        fist and destroy them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You, O God, are my king from ages past,bringing salvation to the
        earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You split the sea by your strengthand smashed the heads of the sea
        monsters.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You crushed the heads of Leviathan[[COMMENT(0)]]and let the desert
        animals eat him.  '
      comments:
      - number: '74:14 '
        content: The identification of Leviathan is disputed, ranging from an earthly
          creature to a mythical sea monster in ancient literature.
    - title: 
      content: 'You caused the springs and streams to gush forth,and you dried up
        rivers that never run dry.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Both day and night belong to you;you made the starlight[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and the sun.  '
      comments:
      - number: '74:16 '
        content: Or <b>moon; </b>Hebrew reads <b>light.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'You set the boundaries of the earth,and you made both summer and
        winter.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'See how these enemies insult you, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.A foolish
        nation has dishonored your name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let these wild beasts destroy your turtledoves.Don\u2019t
        forget your suffering people forever.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember your covenant promises,for the land is full of darkness
        and violence!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let the downtrodden be humiliated again.Instead, let the
        poor and needy praise your name.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Arise, O God, and defend your cause.Remember how these fools insult
        you all day long.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm of Asaph. A song to be sung to the
        tune \u201CDo Not Destroy!\u201D  We thank you, O God!We give thanks because
        you are near.People everywhere tell of your wonderful deeds.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God says, \u201CAt the time I have planned,I will bring justice against
        the wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the earth quakes and its people live in turmoil,I am the one
        who keeps its foundations firm. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI warned the proud, \u2018Stop your boasting!\u2019I told the
        wicked, \u2018Don\u2019t raise your fists!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t raise your fists in defiance at the heavensor speak with
        such arrogance.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For no one on earth\u2014from east or west,or even from the wilderness\u2014should
        raise a defiant fist.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '75:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>should lift.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'It is God alone who judges;he decides who will rise and who will
        fall.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> holds a cup in his handthat is
        full of foaming wine mixed with spices.He pours out the wine in judgment,and
        all the wicked must drink it,draining it to the dregs.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But as for me, I will always proclaim what God has done;I will sing
        praises to the God of Jacob.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of Asaph. A song to be accompanied
        by stringed instruments.  God is honored in Judah;his name is great in Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] is where he lives;Mount Zion is his home.  '
      comments:
      - number: '76:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Salem, </b>another name for Jerusalem.
    - title: 
      content: 'There he has broken the fiery arrows of the enemy,the shields and
        swords and weapons of war. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You are glorious and more majesticthan the everlasting mountains.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '76:4 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>than mountains filled with
          beasts of prey.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Our boldest enemies have been plundered.They lie before us in the
        sleep of death.No warrior could lift a hand against us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At the blast of your breath, O God of Jacob,their horses and chariots
        lay still.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No wonder you are greatly feared!Who can stand before you when your
        anger explodes?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'From heaven you sentenced your enemies;the earth trembled and stood
        silent before you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You stand up to judge those who do evil, O God,and to rescue the
        oppressed of the earth. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Human defiance only enhances your glory,for you use it as a weapon.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '76:10 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'Make vows to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, and keep them.Let
        everyone bring tribute to the Awesome One.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For Jeduthun, the choir director: A psalm of Asaph.  I cry out to
        God; yes, I shout.Oh, that God would listen to me!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When I was in deep trouble,I searched for the Lord.All night long
        I prayed, with hands lifted toward heaven,but my soul was not comforted.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I think of God, and I moan,overwhelmed with longing for his help.
        Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You don\u2019t let me sleep.I am too distressed even to pray!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I think of the good old days,long since ended,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'when my nights were filled with joyful songs.I search my soul and
        ponder the difference now.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Has the Lord rejected me forever?Will he never again be kind to me?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Is his unfailing love gone forever?Have his promises permanently
        failed?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Has God forgotten to be gracious?Has he slammed the door on his compassion?
        Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I said, \u201CThis is my fate;the Most High has turned his hand
        against me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But then I recall all you have done, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;I
        remember your wonderful deeds of long ago.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are constantly in my thoughts.I cannot stop thinking about your
        mighty works.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O God, your ways are holy.Is there any god as mighty as you?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You are the God of great wonders!You demonstrate your awesome power
        among the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'By your strong arm, you redeemed your people,the descendants of Jacob
        and Joseph. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the Red Sea[[COMMENT(0)]] saw you, O God,its waters looked and
        trembled!The sea quaked to its very depths.  '
      comments:
      - number: '77:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the waters.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The clouds poured down rain;the thunder rumbled in the sky.Your arrows
        of lightning flashed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your thunder roared from the whirlwind;the lightning lit up the world!The
        earth trembled and shook.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your road led through the sea,your pathway through the mighty waters\u2014a
        pathway no one knew was there!  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of Asaph.  O my people, listen to my instructions.Open
        your ears to what I am saying,  '
      comments:
      - number: '78:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>maskil. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: "for I will speak to you in a parable.I will teach you hidden lessons
        from our past\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'stories we have heard and known,stories our ancestors handed down
        to us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We will not hide these truths from our children;we will tell the
        next generationabout the glorious deeds of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,about
        his power and his mighty wonders.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he issued his laws to Jacob;he gave his instructions to Israel.He
        commanded our ancestorsto teach them to their children,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "so the next generation might know them\u2014even the children not
        yet born\u2014and they in turn will teach their own children.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So each generation should set its hope anew on God,not forgetting
        his glorious miraclesand obeying his commands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then they will not be like their ancestors\u2014stubborn, rebellious,
        and unfaithful,refusing to give their hearts to God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The warriors of Ephraim, though armed with bows,turned their backs
        and fled on the day of battle.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They did not keep God\u2019s covenantand refused to live by his instructions.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They forgot what he had done\u2014the great wonders he had shown
        them,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the miracles he did for their ancestorson the plain of Zoan in the
        land of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he divided the sea and led them through,making the water stand
        up like walls!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In the daytime he led them by a cloud,and all night by a pillar of
        fire.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He split open the rocks in the wildernessto give them water, as from
        a gushing spring.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He made streams pour from the rock,making the waters flow down like
        a river!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet they kept on sinning against him,rebelling against the Most High
        in the desert.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They stubbornly tested God in their hearts,demanding the foods they
        craved.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They even spoke against God himself, saying,\u201CGod can\u2019t
        give us food in the wilderness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, he can strike a rock so water gushes out,but he can\u2019t give
        his people bread and meat.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> heard them, he was furious.The
        fire of his wrath burned against Jacob.Yes, his anger rose against Israel,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for they did not believe Godor trust him to care for them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But he commanded the skies to open;he opened the doors of heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He rained down manna for them to eat;he gave them bread from heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They ate the food of angels!God gave them all they could hold.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He released the east wind in the heavensand guided the south wind
        by his mighty power.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He rained down meat as thick as dust\u2014birds as plentiful as the
        sand on the seashore!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He caused the birds to fall within their campand all around their
        tents.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people ate their fill.He gave them what they craved.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But before they satisfied their craving,while the meat was yet in
        their mouths,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the anger of God rose against them,and he killed their strongest
        men.He struck down the finest of Israel\u2019s young men.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But in spite of this, the people kept sinning.Despite his wonders,
        they refused to trust him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So he ended their lives in failure,their years in terror.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When God began killing them,they finally sought him.They repented
        and took God seriously.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then they remembered that God was their rock,that God Most High[[COMMENT(0)]]
        was their redeemer.  '
      comments:
      - number: '78:35 '
        content: Hebrew <b>El-Elyon.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But all they gave him was lip service;they lied to him with their
        tongues.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their hearts were not loyal to him.They did not keep his covenant.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet he was merciful and forgave their sinsand did not destroy them
        all.Many times he held back his angerand did not unleash his fury!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he remembered that they were merely mortal,gone like a breath
        of wind that never returns.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Oh, how often they rebelled against him in the wildernessand grieved
        his heart in that dry wasteland.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Again and again they tested God\u2019s patienceand provoked the Holy
        One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They did not remember his powerand how he rescued them from their
        enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They did not remember his miraculous signs in Egypt,his wonders on
        the plain of Zoan.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he turned their rivers into blood,so no one could drink from
        the streams.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He sent vast swarms of flies to consume themand hordes of frogs to
        ruin them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He gave their crops to caterpillars;their harvest was consumed by
        locusts.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He destroyed their grapevines with hailand shattered their sycamore-figs
        with sleet.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He abandoned their cattle to the hail,their livestock to bolts of
        lightning.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He loosed on them his fierce anger\u2014all his fury, rage, and hostility.He
        dispatched against thema band of destroying angels.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He turned his anger against them;he did not spare the Egyptians\u2019
        livesbut ravaged them with the plague.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He killed the oldest son in each Egyptian family,the flower of youth
        throughout the land of Egypt.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '78:51 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in the tents of Ham.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But he led his own people like a flock of sheep,guiding them safely
        through the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He kept them safe so they were not afraid;but the sea covered their
        enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He brought them to the border of his holy land,to this land of hills
        he had won for them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He drove out the nations before them;he gave them their inheritance
        by lot.He settled the tribes of Israel into their homes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But they kept testing and rebelling against God Most High.They did
        not obey his laws.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They turned back and were as faithless as their parents.They were
        as undependable as a crooked bow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They angered God by building shrines to other gods;they made him
        jealous with their idols.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When God heard them, he was very angry,and he completely rejected
        Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then he abandoned his dwelling at Shiloh,the Tabernacle where he
        had lived among the people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He allowed the Ark of his might to be captured;he surrendered his
        glory into enemy hands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He gave his people over to be butchered by the sword,because he was
        so angry with his own people\u2014his special possession.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their young men were killed by fire;their young women died before
        singing their wedding songs.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their priests were slaughtered,and their widows could not mourn their
        deaths.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the Lord rose up as though waking from sleep,like a warrior
        aroused from a drunken stupor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He routed his enemiesand sent them to eternal shame.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But he rejected Joseph\u2019s descendants;he did not choose the tribe
        of Ephraim.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He chose instead the tribe of Judah,and Mount Zion, which he loved.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There he built his sanctuary as high as the heavens,as solid and
        enduring as the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He chose his servant David,calling him from the sheep pens.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He took David from tending the ewes and lambsand made him the shepherd
        of Jacob\u2019s descendants\u2014God\u2019s own people, Israel.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm of Asaph.  O God, pagan nations have conquered your land,your
        special possession.They have defiled your holy Templeand made Jerusalem a
        heap of ruins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have left the bodies of your servantsas food for the birds of
        heaven.The flesh of your godly oneshas become food for the wild animals.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Blood has flowed like water all around Jerusalem;no one is left to
        bury the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are mocked by our neighbors,an object of scorn and derision to
        those around us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, how long will you be angry with us?
        Forever?How long will your jealousy burn like fire?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Pour out your wrath on the nations that refuse to acknowledge you\u2014on
        kingdoms that do not call upon your name.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For they have devoured your people Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]making the
        land a desolate wilderness.  '
      comments:
      - number: '79:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>devoured Jacob. </b>See note on 44:4.
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not hold us guilty for the sins of our ancestors!Let your compassion
        quickly meet our needs,for we are on the brink of despair.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Help us, O God of our salvation!Help us for the glory of your name.Save
        us and forgive our sinsfor the honor of your name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why should pagan nations be allowed to scoff,asking, \u201CWhere
        is their God?\u201DShow us your vengeance against the nations,for they have
        spilled the blood of your servants.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen to the moaning of the prisoners.Demonstrate your great power
        by saving those condemned to die.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O Lord, pay back our neighbors seven timesfor the scorn they have
        hurled at you.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm of Asaph, to be sung to the tune
        \u201CLilies of the Covenant.\u201D  Please listen, O Shepherd of Israel,you
        who lead Joseph\u2019s descendants like a flock.O God, enthroned above the
        cherubim,display your radiant glory  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'to Ephraim, Benjamin, and Manasseh.Show us your mighty power.Come
        to rescue us!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Turn us again to yourself, O God.Make your face shine down upon us.Only
        then will we be saved.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s Armies,how long
        will you be angry with our prayers?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have fed us with sorrowand made us drink tears by the bucketful.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have made us the scorn[[COMMENT(0)]] of neighboring nations.Our
        enemies treat us as a joke.  '
      comments:
      - number: '80:6 '
        content: As in Syriac version; Hebrew reads <b>the strife.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Turn us again to yourself, O God of Heaven\u2019s Armies.Make your
        face shine down upon us.Only then will we be saved.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You brought us from Egypt like a grapevine;you drove away the pagan
        nations and transplanted us into your land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You cleared the ground for us,and we took root and filled the land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our shade covered the mountains;our branches covered the mighty cedars.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We spread our branches west to the Mediterranean Sea;our shoots spread
        east to the Euphrates River.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '80:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>west to the sea, . . . east to the river.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But now, why have you broken down our wallsso that all who pass by
        may steal our fruit?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wild boar from the forest devours it,and the wild animals feed
        on it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come back, we beg you, O God of Heaven\u2019s Armies.Look down from
        heaven and see our plight.Take care of this grapevine  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'that you yourself have planted,this son you have raised for yourself.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For we are chopped up and burned by our enemies.May they perish at
        the sight of your frown.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Strengthen the man you love,the son of your choice.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then we will never abandon you again.Revive us so we can call on
        your name once more.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of Asaph, to be accompanied by a
        stringed instrument.[[COMMENT(0)]]  Sing praises to God, our strength.Sing
        to the God of Jacob.  '
      comments:
      - number: '81:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>according to the gittith.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Sing! Beat the tambourine.Play the sweet lyre and the harp.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Blow the ram\u2019s horn at new moon,and again at full moon to call
        a festival!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For this is required by the decrees of Israel;it is a regulation
        of the God of Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He made it a law for Israel[[COMMENT(0)]]when he attacked Egypt to
        set us free.I heard an unknown voice say,  '
      comments:
      - number: '81:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>for Joseph.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow I will take the load from your shoulders;I will free your
        hands from their heavy tasks.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You cried to me in trouble, and I saved you;I answered out of the
        thundercloudand tested your faith when there was no water at Meribah. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to me, O my people, while I give you stern warnings.O
        Israel, if you would only listen to me!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must never have a foreign god;you must not bow down before a
        false god.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For it was I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,who rescued
        you from the land of Egypt.Open your mouth wide, and I will fill it with
        good things.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut no, my people wouldn\u2019t listen.Israel did not want
        me around.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I let them follow their own stubborn desires,living according
        to their own ideas.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Oh, that my people would listen to me!Oh, that Israel would follow
        me, walking in my paths!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How quickly I would then subdue their enemies!How soon my hands would
        be upon their foes!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who hate the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> would cringe before
        him;they would be doomed forever.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "A psalm of Asaph.  God presides over heaven\u2019s court;he pronounces
        judgment on the heavenly beings:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow long will you hand down unjust decisionsby favoring the
        wicked? Interlude  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGive justice to the poor and the orphan;uphold the rights of
        the oppressed and the destitute.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Rescue the poor and helpless;deliver them from the grasp of evil
        people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But these oppressors know nothing;they are so ignorant!They wander
        about in darkness,while the whole world is shaken to the core.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I say, \u2018You are gods;you are all children of the Most High.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But you will die like mere mortalsand fall like every other ruler.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song. A psalm of Asaph.  O God, do not be silent!Do not be deaf.Do
        not be quiet, O God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t you hear the uproar of your enemies?Don\u2019t you see
        that your arrogant enemies are rising up?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They devise crafty schemes against your people;they conspire against
        your precious ones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCome,\u201D they say, \u201Clet us wipe out Israel as a nation.We
        will destroy the very memory of its existence.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, this was their unanimous decision.They signed a treaty as allies
        against you\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'these Edomites and Ishmaelites;Moabites and Hagrites;  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Gebalites, Ammonites, and Amalekites;and people from Philistia and
        Tyre.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Assyria has joined them, too,and is allied with the descendants of
        Lot. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do to them as you did to the Midianitesand as you did to Sisera and
        Jabin at the Kishon River.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were destroyed at Endor,and their decaying corpses fertilized
        the soil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let their mighty nobles die as Oreb and Zeeb did.Let all their princes
        die like Zebah and Zalmunna,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for they said, \u201CLet us seize for our own usethese pasturelands
        of God!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O my God, scatter them like tumbleweed,like chaff before the wind!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As a fire burns a forestand as a flame sets mountains ablaze,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'chase them with your fierce storm;terrify them with your tempest.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Utterly disgrace themuntil they submit to your name, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them be ashamed and terrified forever.Let them die in disgrace.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm of the descendants of Korah, to be
        accompanied by a stringed instrument.[[COMMENT(0)]]  How lovely is your dwelling
        place,O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments:
      - number: '84:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>according to the gittith.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I long, yes, I faint with longingto enter the courts of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.With
        my whole being, body and soul,I will shout joyfully to the living God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even the sparrow finds a home,and the swallow builds her nest and
        raises her youngat a place near your altar,O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, my King and my God!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What joy for those who can live in your house,always singing your
        praises. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What joy for those whose strength comes from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,who
        have set their minds on a pilgrimage to Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they walk through the Valley of Weeping,[[COMMENT(0)]]it will
        become a place of refreshing springs.The autumn rains will clothe it with
        blessings.  '
      comments:
      - number: '84:6 '
        content: Or <b>Valley of Poplars; </b>Hebrew reads <b>valley of Baca.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'They will continue to grow stronger,and each of them will appear
        before God in Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '84:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s Armies, hear my
        prayer.Listen, O God of Jacob. Interlude  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O God, look with favor upon the king, our shield!Show favor to the
        one you have anointed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A single day in your courtsis better than a thousand anywhere else!I
        would rather be a gatekeeper in the house of my Godthan live the good life
        in the homes of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God is our sun and our shield.He
        gives us grace and glory.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will withhold no
        good thingfrom those who do what is right.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'For the choir director: A psalm of the descendants of Korah.    <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        you poured out blessings on your land!You restored the fortunes of Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '85:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Jacob. </b>See note on 44:4.
    - title: 
      content: "You forgave the guilt of your people\u2014yes, you covered all their
        sins. Interlude  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You held back your fury.You kept back your blazing anger.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now restore us again, O God of our salvation.Put aside your anger
        against us once more.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Will you be angry with us always?Will you prolong your wrath to all
        generations?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Won\u2019t you revive us again,so your people can rejoice in you?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Show us your unfailing love, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and grant
        us your salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I listen carefully to what God the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is
        saying,for he speaks peace to his faithful people.But let them not return
        to their foolish ways.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Surely his salvation is near to those who fear him,so our land will
        be filled with his glory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Unfailing love and truth have met together.Righteousness and peace
        have kissed!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Truth springs up from the earth,and righteousness smiles down from
        heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> pours down his blessings.Our
        land will yield its bountiful harvest.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A prayer of David.  Bend down, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and
        hear my prayer;answer me, for I need your help.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Protect me, for I am devoted to you.Save me, for I serve you and
        trust you.You are my God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Be merciful to me, O Lord,for I am calling on you constantly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give me happiness, O Lord,for I give myself to you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O Lord, you are so good, so ready to forgive,so full of unfailing
        love for all who ask for your help.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen closely to my prayer, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;hear my
        urgent cry.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will call to you whenever I\u2019m in trouble,and you will answer
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No pagan god is like you, O Lord.None can do what you do!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All the nations you madewill come and bow before you, Lord;they will
        praise your holy name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For you are great and perform wonderful deeds.You alone are God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Teach me your ways, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,that I may live
        according to your truth!Grant me purity of heart,so that I may honor you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'With all my heart I will praise you, O Lord my God.I will give glory
        to your name forever,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for your love for me is very great.You have rescued me from the depths
        of death.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '86:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'O God, insolent people rise up against me;a violent gang is trying
        to kill me.You mean nothing to them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you, O Lord,are a God of compassion and mercy,slow to get angryand
        filled with unfailing love and faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look down and have mercy on me.Give your strength to your servant;save
        me, the son of your servant.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song. A psalm of the descendants of Korah.  On the holy mountainstands
        the city founded by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He loves the city of Jerusalemmore than any other city in Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '87:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>He loves the gates of Zion more than all the dwellings
          of Jacob. </b>See note on 44:4.
    - title: 
      content: 'O city of God,what glorious things are said of you! Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will count Egypt[[COMMENT(0)]] and Babylon among those who know
        me\u2014also Philistia and Tyre, and even distant Ethiopia.[[COMMENT(1)]]They
        have all become citizens of Jerusalem!  "
      comments:
      - number: '87:4a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Rahab, </b>the name of a mythical sea monster that represents
          chaos in ancient literature. The name is used here as a poetic name for
          Egypt.
      - number: '87:4b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Cush.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Regarding Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] it will be said,\u201CEveryone
        enjoys the rights of citizenship there.\u201DAnd the Most High will personally
        bless this city.  "
      comments:
      - number: '87:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> registers the nations, he will
        say,\u201CThey have all become citizens of Jerusalem.\u201D Interlude  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm of the descendants of Korah. A song
        to be sung to the tune \u201CThe Suffering of Affliction.\u201D A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of Heman the Ezrahite.  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, God of my salvation,I
        cry out to you by day.I come to you at night.  "
      comments:
      - number: '88:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>maskil. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: 'Now hear my prayer;listen to my cry.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For my life is full of troubles,and death[[COMMENT(0)]] draws near.  '
      comments:
      - number: '88:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I am as good as dead,like a strong man with no strength left.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have left me among the dead,and I lie like a corpse in a grave.I
        am forgotten,cut off from your care.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have thrown me into the lowest pit,into the darkest depths.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your anger weighs me down;with wave after wave you have engulfed
        me. Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have driven my friends awayby making me repulsive to them.I am
        in a trap with no way of escape.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My eyes are blinded by my tears.Each day I beg for your help, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;I
        lift my hands to you for mercy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Are your wonderful deeds of any use to the dead?Do the dead rise
        up and praise you? Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can those in the grave declare your unfailing love?Can they proclaim
        your faithfulness in the place of destruction?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '88:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Abaddon?</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Can the darkness speak of your wonderful deeds?Can anyone in the
        land of forgetfulness talk about your righteousness?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I cry out to you.I will keep on pleading
        day by day.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, why do you reject me?Why do you turn
        your face from me?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have been sick and close to death since my youth.I stand helpless
        and desperate before your terrors.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your fierce anger has overwhelmed me.Your terrors have paralyzed
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They swirl around me like floodwaters all day long.They have engulfed
        me completely.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "A psalm[[COMMENT(0)]] of Ethan the Ezrahite.  I will sing of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s unfailing love forever!Young and old will
        hear of your faithfulness.  "
      comments:
      - number: '89:TITLE '
        content: Hebrew <b>maskil. </b>This may be a literary or musical term.
    - title: 
      content: 'Your unfailing love will last forever.Your faithfulness is as enduring
        as the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CI have made a covenant
        with David, my chosen servant.I have sworn this oath to him:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018I will establish your descendants as kings forever;they will
        sit on your throne from now until eternity.\u2019\u201D Interlude  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All heaven will praise your great wonders, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;myriads
        of angels will praise you for your faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For who in all of heaven can compare with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?What
        mightiest angel is anything like the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The highest angelic powers stand in awe of God.He is far more awesome
        than all who surround his throne.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s Armies!Where is
        there anyone as mighty as you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?You are entirely
        faithful.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You rule the oceans.You subdue their storm-tossed waves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You crushed the great sea monster.[[COMMENT(0)]]You scattered your
        enemies with your mighty arm.  '
      comments:
      - number: '89:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Rahab, </b>the name of a mythical sea monster that represents
          chaos in ancient literature.
    - title: 
      content: "The heavens are yours, and the earth is yours;everything in the world
        is yours\u2014you created it all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You created north and south.Mount Tabor and Mount Hermon praise your
        name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Powerful is your arm!Strong is your hand!Your right hand is lifted
        high in glorious strength.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Righteousness and justice are the foundation of your throne.Unfailing
        love and truth walk before you as attendants.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Happy are those who hear the joyful call to worship,for they will
        walk in the light of your presence, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They rejoice all day long in your wonderful reputation.They exult
        in your righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You are their glorious strength.It pleases you to make us strong.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, our protection comes from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        he, the Holy One of Israel, has given us our king.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Long ago you spoke in a vision to your faithful people.You said,
        \u201CI have raised up a warrior.I have selected him from the common people
        to be king.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have found my servant David.I have anointed him with my holy oil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will steady him with my hand;with my powerful arm I will make him
        strong.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His enemies will not defeat him,nor will the wicked overpower him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will beat down his adversaries before himand destroy those who
        hate him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My faithfulness and unfailing love will be with him,and by my authority
        he will grow in power.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will extend his rule over the sea,his dominion over the rivers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And he will call out to me, \u2018You are my Father,my God, and the
        Rock of my salvation.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will make him my firstborn son,the mightiest king on earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will love him and be kind to him forever;my covenant with him will
        never end.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will preserve an heir for him;his throne will be as endless as
        the days of heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if his descendants forsake my instructionsand fail to obey my
        regulations,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'if they do not obey my decreesand fail to keep my commands,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then I will punish their sin with the rod,and their disobedience
        with beating.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I will never stop loving himnor fail to keep my promise to him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, I will not break my covenant;I will not take back a single word
        I said.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have sworn an oath to David,and in my holiness I cannot lie:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His dynasty will go on forever;his kingdom will endure as the sun.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It will be as eternal as the moon,my faithful witness in the sky!\u201D
        Interlude  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now you have rejected him and cast him off.You are angry with
        your anointed king.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have renounced your covenant with him;you have thrown his crown
        in the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have broken down the walls protecting himand ruined every fort
        defending him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Everyone who comes along has robbed him,and he has become a joke
        to his neighbors.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have strengthened his enemiesand made them all rejoice.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have made his sword uselessand refused to help him in battle.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have ended his splendorand overturned his throne.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have made him old before his timeand publicly disgraced him.
        Interlude  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, how long will this go on?Will you
        hide yourself forever?How long will your anger burn like fire?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember how short my life is,how empty and futile this human existence!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No one can live forever; all will die.No one can escape the power
        of the grave.[[COMMENT(0)]]  Interlude  '
      comments:
      - number: '89:48 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Lord, where is your unfailing love?You promised it to David with
        a faithful pledge.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Consider, Lord, how your servants are disgraced!I carry in my heart
        the insults of so many people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your enemies have mocked me, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;they mock
        your anointed king wherever he goes.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "  Book Four (Psalms 90\u2013106)"
      content: 'A prayer of Moses, the man of God.  Lord, through all the generationsyou
        have been our home!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Before the mountains were born,before you gave birth to the earth
        and the world,from beginning to end, you are God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You turn people back to dust, saying,\u201CReturn to dust, you mortals!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For you, a thousand years are as a passing day,as brief as a few
        night hours.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You sweep people away like dreams that disappear.They are like grass
        that springs up in the morning.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In the morning it blooms and flourishes,but by evening it is dry
        and withered.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We wither beneath your anger;we are overwhelmed by your fury.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You spread out our sins before you\u2014our secret sins\u2014and
        you see them all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We live our lives beneath your wrath,ending our years with a groan.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Seventy years are given to us!Some even live to eighty.But even the
        best years are filled with pain and trouble;soon they disappear, and we fly
        away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who can comprehend the power of your anger?Your wrath is as awesome
        as the fear you deserve.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Teach us to realize the brevity of life,so that we may grow in wisdom.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, come back to us!How long will you
        delay?Take pity on your servants!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Satisfy us each morning with your unfailing love,so we may sing for
        joy to the end of our lives.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give us gladness in proportion to our former misery!Replace the evil
        years with good.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let us, your servants, see you work again;let our children see your
        glory.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Those who live in the shelter of the Most Highwill find rest in
        the shadow of the Almighty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This I declare about the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:He alone is
        my refuge, my place of safety;he is my God, and I trust him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he will rescue you from every trapand protect you from deadly
        disease.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will cover you with his feathers.He will shelter you with his
        wings.His faithful promises are your armor and protection.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not be afraid of the terrors of the night,nor the arrow that flies
        in the day.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not dread the disease that stalks in darkness,nor the disaster
        that strikes at midday.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though a thousand fall at your side,though ten thousand are dying
        around you,these evils will not touch you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Just open your eyes,and see how the wicked are punished.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you make the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your refuge,if you make
        the Most High your shelter,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'no evil will conquer you;no plague will come near your home.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he will order his angelsto protect you wherever you go.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will hold you up with their handsso you won\u2019t even hurt
        your foot on a stone.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will trample upon lions and cobras;you will crush fierce lions
        and serpents under your feet!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CI will rescue those who
        love me.I will protect those who trust in my name.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they call on me, I will answer;I will be with them in trouble.I
        will rescue and honor them.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm. A song to be sung on the Sabbath Day.  It is good to give
        thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,to sing praises to the Most High.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is good to proclaim your unfailing love in the morning,your faithfulness
        in the evening,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'accompanied by a ten-stringed instrument, a harp,and the melody of
        a lyre.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You thrill me, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, with all you have done
        for me!I sing for joy because of what you have done.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, what great works you do!And how deep
        are your thoughts.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Only a simpleton would not know,and only a fool would not understand
        this:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though the wicked sprout like weedsand evildoers flourish,they will
        be destroyed forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, will be exalted forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your enemies, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, will surely perish;all
        evildoers will be scattered.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you have made me as strong as a wild ox.You have anointed me
        with the finest oil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My eyes have seen the downfall of my enemies;my ears have heard the
        defeat of my wicked opponents.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the godly will flourish like palm treesand grow strong like the
        cedars of Lebanon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For they are transplanted to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        own house.They flourish in the courts of our God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even in old age they will still produce fruit;they will remain vital
        and green.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is king! He is robed in majesty.Indeed,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is robed in majesty and armed with strength.The
        world stands firmand cannot be shaken.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your throne, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, has stood from time immemorial.You
        yourself are from the everlasting past.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The floods have risen up, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.The floods
        have roared like thunder;the floods have lifted their pounding waves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But mightier than the violent raging of the seas,mightier than the
        breakers on the shore\u2014the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> above is mightier
        than these!  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of vengeance,O God of vengeance,
        let your glorious justice shine forth!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Arise, O Judge of the earth.Give the proud what they deserve.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How long, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?How long will the wicked
        be allowed to gloat?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How long will they speak with arrogance?How long will these evil
        people boast?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They crush your people, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,hurting those
        you claim as your own.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They kill widows and foreignersand murder orphans.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>isn\u2019t looking,\u201D they
        say,\u201Cand besides, the God of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] doesn\u2019t care.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '94:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Jacob. </b>See note on 44:4.
    - title: 
      content: 'Think again, you fools!When will you finally catch on?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Is he deaf\u2014the one who made your ears?Is he blind\u2014the one
        who formed your eyes?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He punishes the nations\u2014won\u2019t he also punish you?He knows
        everything\u2014doesn\u2019t he also know what you are doing?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> knows people\u2019s thoughts;he knows
        they are worthless!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Joyful are those you discipline, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,those
        you teach with your instructions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You give them relief from troubled timesuntil a pit is dug to capture
        the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not reject his people;he will
        not abandon his special possession.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Judgment will again be founded on justice,and those with virtuous
        hearts will pursue it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who will protect me from the wicked?Who will stand up for me against
        evildoers?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Unless the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had helped me,I would soon
        have settled in the silence of the grave.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I cried out, \u201CI am slipping!\u201Dbut your unfailing love, O
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, supported me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When doubts filled my mind,your comfort gave me renewed hope and
        cheer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can unjust leaders claim that God is on their side\u2014leaders whose
        decrees permit injustice?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They gang up against the righteousand condemn the innocent to death.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is my fortress;my God is the
        mighty rock where I hide.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Come, let us sing to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Let us shout
        joyfully to the Rock of our salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let us come to him with thanksgiving.Let us sing psalms of praise
        to him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is a great God,a great King above
        all gods.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He holds in his hands the depths of the earthand the mightiest mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The sea belongs to him, for he made it.His hands formed the dry land,
        too.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Come, let us worship and bow down.Let us kneel before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our maker,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for he is our God.We are the people he watches over,the flock under
        his care.If only you would listen to his voice today!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CDon\u2019t harden your
        hearts as Israel did at Meribah,as they did at Massah in the wilderness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For there your ancestors tested and tried my patience,even though
        they saw everything I did.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For forty years I was angry with them, and I said,\u2018They are
        a people whose hearts turn away from me.They refuse to do what I tell them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Sing a new song to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Let the whole
        earth sing to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sing to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; praise his name.Each day
        proclaim the good news that he saves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Publish his glorious deeds among the nations.Tell everyone about
        the amazing things he does.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Great is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>! He is most worthy of praise!He
        is to be feared above all gods.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The gods of other nations are mere idols,but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        made the heavens!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Honor and majesty surround him;strength and beauty fill his sanctuary.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O nations of the world, recognize the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;recognize
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is glorious and strong.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> the glory he deserves!Bring
        your offering and come into his courts.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in all his holy splendor.Let
        all the earth tremble before him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Tell all the nations, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> reigns!\u201DThe
        world stands firm and cannot be shaken.He will judge all peoples fairly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the heavens be glad, and the earth rejoice!Let the sea and everything
        in it shout his praise!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the fields and their crops burst out with joy!Let the trees of
        the forest sing for joy  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is king!Let the earth rejoice!Let
        the farthest coastlands be glad.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Dark clouds surround him.Righteousness and justice are the foundation
        of his throne.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Fire spreads ahead of himand burns up all his foes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His lightning flashes out across the world.The earth sees and trembles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The mountains melt like wax before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,before
        the Lord of all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The heavens proclaim his righteousness;every nation sees his glory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who worship idols are disgraced\u2014all who brag about their
        worthless gods\u2014for every god must bow to him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] has heard and rejoiced,and all the towns
        of Judah are gladbecause of your justice, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!  '
      comments:
      - number: '97:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, are supreme over all the
        earth;you are exalted far above all gods.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You who love the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, hate evil!He protects
        the lives of his godly peopleand rescues them from the power of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Light shines on the godly,and joy on those whose hearts are right.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm.  Sing a new song to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,for
        he has done wonderful deeds.His right hand has won a mighty victory;his holy
        arm has shown his saving power!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has announced his victoryand has
        revealed his righteousness to every nation!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has remembered his promise to love and be faithful to Israel.The
        ends of the earth have seen the victory of our God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Shout to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, all the earth;break out
        in praise and sing for joy!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sing your praise to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with the harp,with
        the harp and melodious song,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "with trumpets and the sound of the ram\u2019s horn.Make a joyful
        symphony before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the King!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the sea and everything in it shout his praise!Let the earth and
        all living things join in.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the rivers clap their hands in glee!Let the hills sing out their
        songs of joy  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is king!Let the nations tremble!He
        sits on his throne between the cherubim.Let the whole earth quake!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sits in majesty in Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]]exalted
        above all the nations.  '
      comments:
      - number: '99:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them praise your great and awesome name.Your name is holy!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Mighty King, lover of justice,you have established fairness.You have
        acted with justiceand righteousness throughout Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '99:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jacob. </b>See note on 44:4.
    - title: 
      content: 'Exalt the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God!Bow low before his
        feet, for he is holy!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Moses and Aaron were among his priests;Samuel also called on his
        name.They cried to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for help,and he answered
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He spoke to Israel from the pillar of cloud,and they followed the
        laws and decrees he gave them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, you answered them.You were
        a forgiving God to them,but you punished them when they went wrong.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm of thanksgiving.  Shout with joy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        all the earth!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with gladness.Come before
        him, singing with joy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Acknowledge that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is God!He made us,
        and we are his.[[COMMENT(0)]]We are his people, the sheep of his pasture.  '
      comments:
      - number: '100:3 '
        content: As in an alternate reading in the Masoretic Text; the other alternate
          and some ancient versions read <b>and not we ourselves.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Enter his gates with thanksgiving;go into his courts with praise.Give
        thanks to him and praise his name.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm of David.  I will sing of your love and justice, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.I
        will praise you with songs.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will be careful to live a blameless life\u2014when will you come
        to help me?I will lead a life of integrityin my own home.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will refuse to look atanything vile and vulgar.I hate all who deal
        crookedly;I will have nothing to do with them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will reject perverse ideasand stay away from every evil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will not tolerate people who slander their neighbors.I will not
        endure conceit and pride.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will search for faithful peopleto be my companions.Only those who
        are above reproachwill be allowed to serve me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will not allow deceivers to serve in my house,and liars will not
        stay in my presence.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A prayer of one overwhelmed with trouble, pouring out problems before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.    <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, hear my
        prayer!Listen to my plea!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t turn away from mein my time of distress.Bend down to listen,and
        answer me quickly when I call to you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For my days disappear like smoke,and my bones burn like red-hot coals.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My heart is sick, withered like grass,and I have lost my appetite.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because of my groaning,I am reduced to skin and bones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am like an owl in the desert,like a little owl in a far-off wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I lie awake,lonely as a solitary bird on the roof.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My enemies taunt me day after day.They mock and curse me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I eat ashes for food.My tears run down into my drink  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'because of your anger and wrath.For you have picked me up and thrown
        me out.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My life passes as swiftly as the evening shadows.I am withering away
        like grass.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, will sit on your throne forever.Your
        fame will endure to every generation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will arise and have mercy on Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014and
        now is the time to pity her,now is the time you promised to help.  "
      comments:
      - number: '102:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion; </b>also in 102:16.
    - title: 
      content: 'For your people love every stone in her wallsand cherish even the
        dust in her streets.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the nations will tremble before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.The
        kings of the earth will tremble before his glory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will rebuild Jerusalem.He will
        appear in his glory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will listen to the prayers of the destitute.He will not reject
        their pleas.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let this be recorded for future generations,so that a people not
        yet born will praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Tell them the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> looked downfrom his heavenly
        sanctuary.He looked down to earth from heaven  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'to hear the groans of the prisoners,to release those condemned to
        die.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And so the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s fame will be celebrated
        in Zion,his praises in Jerusalem,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'when multitudes gather togetherand kingdoms come to worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He broke my strength in midlife,cutting short my days.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I cried to him, \u201CO my God, who lives forever,don\u2019t
        take my life while I am so young!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Long ago you laid the foundation of the earthand made the heavens
        with your hands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will perish, but you remain forever;they will wear out like
        old clothing.You will change them like a garmentand discard them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you are always the same;you will live forever.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A psalm of David.  Let all that I am praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;with
        my whole heart, I will praise his holy name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let all that I am praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;may I never
        forget the good things he does for me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He forgives all my sinsand heals all my diseases.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He redeems me from deathand crowns me with love and tender mercies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He fills my life with good things.My youth is renewed like the eagle\u2019s!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gives righteousnessand justice to
        all who are treated unfairly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He revealed his character to Mosesand his deeds to the people of
        Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is compassionate and merciful,slow
        to get angry and filled with unfailing love.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will not constantly accuse us,nor remain angry forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He does not punish us for all our sins;he does not deal harshly with
        us, as we deserve.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For his unfailing love toward those who fear himis as great as the
        height of the heavens above the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has removed our sins as far from usas the east is from the west.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is like a father to his children,tender
        and compassionate to those who fear him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he knows how weak we are;he remembers we are only dust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our days on earth are like grass;like wildflowers, we bloom and die.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The wind blows, and we are gone\u2014as though we had never been
        here.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the love of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> remains foreverwith
        those who fear him.His salvation extends to the children\u2019s children  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'of those who are faithful to his covenant,of those who obey his commandments!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has made the heavens his throne;from
        there he rules over everything.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you angels,you mighty ones
        who carry out his plans,listening for each of his commands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you armies of angelswho
        serve him and do his will!  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Let all that I am praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        my God, how great you are!You are robed with honor and majesty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You are dressed in a robe of light.You stretch out the starry curtain
        of the heavens;  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'you lay out the rafters of your home in the rain clouds.You make
        the clouds your chariot;you ride upon the wings of the wind.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The winds are your messengers;flames of fire are your servants.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '104:4 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>He sends his angels like the winds, / his
          servants like flames of fire. </b>Compare Heb 1:7.
    - title: 
      content: 'You placed the world on its foundationso it would never be moved.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You clothed the earth with floods of water,water that covered even
        the mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At your command, the water fled;at the sound of your thunder, it
        hurried away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Mountains rose and valleys sankto the levels you decreed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you set a firm boundary for the seas,so they would never again
        cover the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You make springs pour water into the ravines,so streams gush down
        from the mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They provide water for all the animals,and the wild donkeys quench
        their thirst.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The birds nest beside the streamsand sing among the branches of the
        trees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You send rain on the mountains from your heavenly home,and you fill
        the earth with the fruit of your labor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You cause grass to grow for the livestockand plants for people to
        use.You allow them to produce food from the earth\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'wine to make them glad,olive oil to soothe their skin,and bread to
        give them strength.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The trees of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> are well cared for\u2014the
        cedars of Lebanon that he planted.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There the birds make their nests,and the storks make their homes
        in the cypresses.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'High in the mountains live the wild goats,and the rocks form a refuge
        for the hyraxes.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '104:18 '
        content: Or <b>coneys, </b>or <b>rock badgers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'You made the moon to mark the seasons,and the sun knows when to set.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You send the darkness, and it becomes night,when all the forest animals
        prowl about.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the young lions roar for their prey,stalking the food provided
        by God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At dawn they slink backinto their dens to rest.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then people go off to their work,where they labor until evening.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, what a variety of things you have
        made!In wisdom you have made them all.The earth is full of your creatures.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Here is the ocean, vast and wide,teeming with life of every kind,both
        large and small.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'See the ships sailing along,and Leviathan,[[COMMENT(0)]] which you
        made to play in the sea.  '
      comments:
      - number: '104:26 '
        content: The identification of Leviathan is disputed, ranging from an earthly
          creature to a mythical sea monster in ancient literature.
    - title: 
      content: 'They all depend on youto give them food as they need it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you supply it, they gather it.You open your hand to feed them,and
        they are richly satisfied.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if you turn away from them, they panic.When you take away their
        breath,they die and turn again to dust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you give them your breath,[[COMMENT(0)]] life is created,and
        you renew the face of the earth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '104:30 '
        content: Or <b>When you send your Spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'May the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> continue forever!The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> takes pleasure in all he has made!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The earth trembles at his glance;the mountains smoke at his touch.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will sing to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> as long as I live.I
        will praise my God to my last breath!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May all my thoughts be pleasing to him,for I rejoice in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Give thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and proclaim his
        greatness.Let the whole world know what he has done.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sing to him; yes, sing his praises.Tell everyone about his wonderful
        deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Exult in his holy name;rejoice, you who worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Search for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and for his strength;continually
        seek him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember the wonders he has performed,his miracles, and the rulings
        he has given,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'you children of his servant Abraham,you descendants of Jacob, his
        chosen ones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God.His justice is seen
        throughout the land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He always stands by his covenant\u2014the commitment he made to a
        thousand generations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is the covenant he made with Abrahamand the oath he swore to
        Isaac.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He confirmed it to Jacob as a decree,and to the people of Israel
        as a never-ending covenant:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will give you the land of Canaanas your special possession.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He said this when they were few in number,a tiny group of strangers
        in Canaan.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They wandered from nation to nation,from one kingdom to another.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet he did not let anyone oppress them.He warned kings on their behalf:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDo not touch my chosen people,and do not hurt my prophets.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He called for a famine on the land of Canaan,cutting off its food
        supply.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he sent someone to Egypt ahead of them\u2014Joseph, who was
        sold as a slave.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They bruised his feet with fettersand placed his neck in an iron
        collar.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Until the time came to fulfill his dreams,[[COMMENT(0)]]the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        tested Joseph\u2019s character.  "
