      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Give thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        for he is good!His faithful love endures forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who can list the glorious miracles of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?Who
        can ever praise him enough?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There is joy for those who deal justly with othersand always do what
        is right.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember me, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, when you show favor to
        your people;come near and rescue me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let me share in the prosperity of your chosen ones.Let me rejoice
        in the joy of your people;let me praise you with those who are your heritage.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Like our ancestors, we have sinned.We have done wrong! We have acted
        wickedly!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Our ancestors in Egyptwere not impressed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        miraculous deeds.They soon forgot his many acts of kindness to them.Instead,
        they rebelled against him at the Red Sea.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '106:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>at the sea, the sea of reeds.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Even so, he saved them\u2014to defend the honor of his nameand to
        demonstrate his mighty power.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He commanded the Red Sea[[COMMENT(0)]] to dry up.He led Israel across
        the sea as if it were a desert.  '
      comments:
      - number: '106:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>sea of reeds; </b>also in 106:22.
    - title: 
      content: 'So he rescued them from their enemiesand redeemed them from their
        foes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the water returned and covered their enemies;not one of them
        survived.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then his people believed his promises.Then they sang his praise.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet how quickly they forgot what he had done!They wouldn\u2019t wait
        for his counsel!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the wilderness their desires ran wild,testing God\u2019s patience
        in that dry wasteland.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So he gave them what they asked for,but he sent a plague along with
        it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people in the camp were jealous of Mosesand envious of Aaron,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s holy priest.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because of this, the earth opened up;it swallowed Dathanand buried
        Abiram and the other rebels.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Fire fell upon their followers;a flame consumed the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people made a calf at Mount Sinai[[COMMENT(0)]];they bowed before
        an image made of gold.  '
      comments:
      - number: '106:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>at Horeb, </b>another name for Sinai.
    - title: 
      content: 'They traded their glorious Godfor a statue of a grass-eating bull.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They forgot God, their savior,who had done such great things in Egypt\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'such wonderful things in the land of Ham,such awesome deeds at the
        Red Sea.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So he declared he would destroy them.But Moses, his chosen one, stepped
        between the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and the people.He begged him to turn
        from his anger and not destroy them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people refused to enter the pleasant land,for they wouldn\u2019t
        believe his promise to care for them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, they grumbled in their tentsand refused to obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, he solemnly sworethat he would kill them in the wilderness,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'that he would scatter their descendants[[COMMENT(0)]] among the nations,exiling
        them to distant lands.  '
      comments:
      - number: '106:27 '
        content: As in Syriac version; Hebrew reads <b>he would cause their descendants
          to fall.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then our ancestors joined in the worship of Baal at Peor;they even
        ate sacrifices offered to the dead!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They angered the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with all these things,so
        a plague broke out among them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But Phinehas had the courage to intervene,and the plague was stopped.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So he has been regarded as a righteous manever since that time.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At Meribah, too, they angered the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,causing
        Moses serious trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They made Moses angry,[[COMMENT(0)]]and he spoke foolishly.  '
      comments:
      - number: '106:33 '
        content: Hebrew <b>They embittered his spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Israel failed to destroy the nations in the land,as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, they mingled among the pagansand adopted their evil customs.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They worshiped their idols,which led to their downfall.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They even sacrificed their sonsand their daughters to the demons.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They shed innocent blood,the blood of their sons and daughters.By
        sacrificing them to the idols of Canaan,they polluted the land with murder.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They defiled themselves by their evil deeds,and their love of idols
        was adultery in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s sight.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger burned against
        his people,and he abhorred his own special possession.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He handed them over to pagan nations,and they were ruled by those
        who hated them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their enemies crushed themand brought them under their cruel power.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Again and again he rescued them,but they chose to rebel against him,and
        they were finally destroyed by their sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even so, he pitied them in their distressand listened to their cries.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He remembered his covenant with themand relented because of his unfailing
        love.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He even caused their captorsto treat them with kindness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Save us, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God!Gather us back from
        among the nations,so we can thank your holy nameand rejoice and praise you.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "  Book Five (Psalms 107\u2013150)"
      content: '  Give thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for he is good!His
        faithful love endures forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> redeemed you? Then speak out!Tell
        others he has redeemed you from your enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he has gathered the exiles from many lands,from east and west,from
        north and south.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '107:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>and sea.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Some wandered in the wilderness,lost and homeless.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Hungry and thirsty,they nearly died.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, help!\u201D they cried in their
        trouble,and he rescued them from their distress.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He led them straight to safety,to a city where they could live.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for his great loveand
        for the wonderful things he has done for them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he satisfies the thirstyand fills the hungry with good things.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some sat in darkness and deepest gloom,imprisoned in iron chains
