      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for his great loveand
        for the wonderful things he has done for them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he broke down their prison gates of bronze;he cut apart their
        bars of iron.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some were fools; they rebelledand suffered for their sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They couldn\u2019t stand the thought of food,and they were knocking
        on death\u2019s door.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, help!\u201D they cried in their
        trouble,and he saved them from their distress.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He sent out his word and healed them,snatching them from the door
        of death.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for his great loveand
        for the wonderful things he has done for them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them offer sacrifices of thanksgivingand sing joyfully about
        his glorious acts.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some went off to sea in ships,plying the trade routes of the world.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They, too, observed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s power
        in action,his impressive works on the deepest seas.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He spoke, and the winds rose,stirring up the waves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their ships were tossed to the heavensand plunged again to the depths;the
        sailors cringed in terror.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They reeled and staggered like drunkardsand were at their wits\u2019
        end.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, help!\u201D they cried in their
        trouble,and he saved them from their distress.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He calmed the storm to a whisperand stilled the waves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What a blessing was that stillnessas he brought them safely into
        harbor!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for his great loveand
        for the wonderful things he has done for them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them exalt him publicly before the congregationand before the
        leaders of the nation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He changes rivers into deserts,and springs of water into dry, thirsty
        land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He turns the fruitful land into salty wastelands,because of the wickedness
        of those who live there.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But he also turns deserts into pools of water,the dry land into springs
        of water.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He brings the hungry to settle thereand to build their cities.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They sow their fields, plant their vineyards,and harvest their bumper
        crops.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How he blesses them!They raise large families there,and their herds
        of livestock increase.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they decrease in number and become impoverishedthrough oppression,
        trouble, and sorrow,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> pours contempt on their princes,causing
        them to wander in trackless wastelands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But he rescues the poor from troubleand increases their families
        like flocks of sheep.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godly will see these things and be glad,while the wicked are
        struck silent.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song. A psalm of David.  My heart is confident in you, O God;no
        wonder I can sing your praises with all my heart!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wake up, lyre and harp!I will wake the dawn with my song.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will thank you, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, among all the people.I
        will sing your praises among the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For your unfailing love is higher than the heavens.Your faithfulness
        reaches to the clouds.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Be exalted, O God, above the highest heavens.May your glory shine
        over all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now rescue your beloved people.Answer and save us by your power.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God has promised this by his holiness[[COMMENT(0)]]:\u201CI will
        divide up Shechem with joy.I will measure out the valley of Succoth.  "
      comments:
      - number: '108:7 '
        content: Or <b>in his sanctuary.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Gilead is mine,and Manasseh, too.Ephraim, my helmet, will produce
        my warriors,and Judah, my scepter, will produce my kings.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Moab, my washbasin, will become my servant,and I will wipe my
        feet on Edomand shout in triumph over Philistia.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who will bring me into the fortified city?Who will bring me victory
        over Edom?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Have you rejected us, O God?Will you no longer march with our armies?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Oh, please help us against our enemies,for all human help is useless.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "For the choir director: A psalm of David.  O God, whom I praise,don\u2019t
        stand silent and aloof  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'while the wicked slander meand tell lies about me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They surround me with hateful wordsand fight against me for no reason.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I love them, but they try to destroy me with accusationseven as I
        am praying for them!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They repay evil for good,and hatred for my love.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They say,[[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CGet an evil person to turn against
        him.Send an accuser to bring him to trial.  "
      comments:
      - number: '109:6 '
        content: Hebrew lacks <b>They say.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'When his case comes up for judgment,let him be pronounced guilty.Count
        his prayers as sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let his years be few;let someone else take his position.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May his children become fatherless,and his wife a widow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May his children wander as beggarsand be driven from[[COMMENT(0)]]
        their ruined homes.  '
      comments:
      - number: '109:10 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>and seek.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'May creditors seize his entire estate,and strangers take all he has
        earned.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let no one be kind to him;let no one pity his fatherless children.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May all his offspring die.May his family name be blotted out in the
        next generation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> never forget the sins of his
        fathers;may his mother\u2019s sins never be erased from the record.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> always remember these sins,and
        may his name disappear from human memory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he refused all kindness to others;he persecuted the poor and
        needy,and he hounded the brokenhearted to death.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He loved to curse others;now you curse him.He never blessed others;now
        don\u2019t you bless him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Cursing is as natural to him as his clothing,or the water he drinks,or
        the rich food he eats.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now may his curses return and cling to him like clothing;may they
        be tied around him like a belt.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "May those curses become the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s punishmentfor
        my accusers who speak evil of me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But deal well with me, O Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,for
        the sake of your own reputation!Rescue mebecause you are so faithful and
        good.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I am poor and needy,and my heart is full of pain.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am fading like a shadow at dusk;I am brushed off like a locust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My knees are weak from fasting,and I am skin and bones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am a joke to people everywhere;when they see me, they shake their
        heads in scorn.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Help me, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God!Save me because of
        your unfailing love.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them see that this is your doing,that you yourself have done
        it, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then let them curse me if they like,but you will bless me!When they
        attack me, they will be disgraced!But I, your servant, will go right on rejoicing!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May my accusers be clothed with disgrace;may their humiliation cover
        them like a cloak.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I will give repeated thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,praising
        him to everyone.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "A psalm of David.  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to my Lord,[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CSit
        in the place of honor at my right handuntil I humble your enemies,making
        them a footstool under your feet.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '110:1 '
        content: Or <b>my lord.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will extend your powerful kingdom
        from Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]];you will rule over your enemies.  '
      comments:
      - number: '110:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'When you go to war,your people will serve you willingly.You are arrayed
        in holy garments,and your strength will be renewed each day like the morning
        dew.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has taken an oath and will not break
        his vow:\u201CYou are a priest forever in the order of Melchizedek.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Lord stands at your right hand to protect you.He will strike
        down many kings when his anger erupts.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will punish the nationsand fill their lands with corpses;he will
        shatter heads over the whole earth.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]]  Praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!I will thank
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with all my heartas I meet with his godly
        people.  '
      comments:
      - number: '111 '
        content: '  This psalm is a Hebrew acrostic poem; after the introductory
          note of praise, each line begins with a successive letter of the Hebrew
          alphabet.  '
    - title: 
      content: 'How amazing are the deeds of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!All
        who delight in him should ponder them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Everything he does reveals his glory and majesty.His righteousness
        never fails.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He causes us to remember his wonderful works.How gracious and merciful
        is our <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He gives food to those who fear him;he always remembers his covenant.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has shown his great power to his peopleby giving them the lands
        of other nations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All he does is just and good,and all his commandments are trustworthy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are forever true,to be obeyed faithfully and with integrity.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
