        of your laws.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am even wiser than my elders,for I have kept your commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have refused to walk on any evil path,so that I may remain obedient
        to your word.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I haven\u2019t turned away from your regulations,for you have taught
        me well.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How sweet your words taste to me;they are sweeter than honey.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Nun
      content: 'Your commandments give me understanding;no wonder I hate every false
        way of life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your word is a lamp to guide my feetand a light for my path.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I\u2019ve promised it once, and I\u2019ll promise it again:I will
        obey your righteous regulations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have suffered much, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;restore my life
        again as you promised.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, accept my offering of praise,and teach
        me your regulations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My life constantly hangs in the balance,but I will not stop obeying
        your instructions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked have set their traps for me,but I will not turn from your
        commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your laws are my treasure;they are my heart\u2019s delight.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Samekh
      content: 'I am determined to keep your decreesto the very end.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I hate those with divided loyalties,but I love your instructions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You are my refuge and my shield;your word is my source of hope.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Get out of my life, you evil-minded people,for I intend to obey the
        commands of my God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, sustain me as you promised, that I
        may live!Do not let my hope be crushed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sustain me, and I will be rescued;then I will meditate continually
        on your decrees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you have rejected all who stray from your decrees.They are only
        fooling themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You skim off the wicked of the earth like scum;no wonder I love to
        obey your laws!  '
      comments: []
    - title: Ayin
      content: 'I tremble in fear of you;I stand in awe of your regulations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t leave me to the mercy of my enemies,for I have done what
        is just and right.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Please guarantee a blessing for me.Don\u2019t let the arrogant oppress
        me!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My eyes strain to see your rescue,to see the truth of your promise
        fulfilled.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am your servant; deal with me in unfailing love,and teach me your
        decrees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give discernment to me, your servant;then I will understand your
        laws.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, it is time for you to act,for these
        evil people have violated your instructions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Truly, I love your commandsmore than gold, even the finest gold.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Pe
      content: 'Each of your commandments is right.That is why I hate every false
        way.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your laws are wonderful.No wonder I obey them!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The teaching of your word gives light,so even the simple can understand.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I pant with expectation,longing for your commands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Come and show me your mercy,as you do for all who love your name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Guide my steps by your word,so I will not be overcome by evil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Ransom me from the oppression of evil people;then I can obey your
        commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look upon me with love;teach me your decrees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Tsadhe
      content: 'Rivers of tears gush from my eyesbecause people disobey your instructions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you are righteous,and your regulations
        are fair.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your laws are perfectand completely trustworthy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am overwhelmed with indignation,for my enemies have disregarded
        your words.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your promises have been thoroughly tested;that is why I love them
        so much.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am insignificant and despised,but I don\u2019t forget your commandments.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your justice is eternal,and your instructions are perfectly true.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As pressure and stress bear down on me,I find joy in your commands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Qoph
      content: 'Your laws are always right;help me to understand them so I may live.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I pray with all my heart; answer me, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!I
        will obey your decrees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I cry out to you; rescue me,that I may obey your laws.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I rise early, before the sun is up;I cry out for help and put my
        hope in your words.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I stay awake through the night,thinking about your promise.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In your faithful love, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, hear my cry;let
        me be revived by following your regulations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lawless people are coming to attack me;they live far from your instructions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you are near, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and all your commands
        are true.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Resh
      content: 'I have known from my earliest daysthat your laws will last forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look upon my suffering and rescue me,for I have not forgotten your
        instructions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Argue my case; take my side!Protect my life as you promised.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked are far from rescue,for they do not bother with your decrees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, how great is your mercy;let me be
        revived by following your regulations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Many persecute and trouble me,yet I have not swerved from your laws.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Seeing these traitors makes me sick at heart,because they care nothing
        for your word.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'See how I love your commandments, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Give
        back my life because of your unfailing love.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Shin
      content: 'The very essence of your words is truth;all your just regulations
        will stand forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Powerful people harass me without cause,but my heart trembles only
        at your word.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I rejoice in your wordlike one who discovers a great treasure.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I hate and abhor all falsehood,but I love your instructions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will praise you seven times a daybecause all your regulations are
        just.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who love your instructions have great peaceand do not stumble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I long for your rescue, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,so I have obeyed
        your commands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have obeyed your laws,for I love them very much.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Taw
      content: 'Yes, I obey your commandments and lawsbecause you know everything
        I do.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, listen to my cry;give me the discerning
        mind you promised.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen to my prayer;rescue me as you promised.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let praise flow from my lips,for you have taught me your decrees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let my tongue sing about your word,for all your commands are right.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give me a helping hand,for I have chosen to follow your commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I have longed for your rescue,and
        your instructions are my delight.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let me live so I can praise you,and may your regulations help me.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem.  I took my troubles to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;I cried out to him, and he answered my prayer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Rescue me, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, from liarsand from all
        deceitful people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O deceptive tongue, what will God do to you?How will he increase
        your punishment?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will be pierced with sharp arrowsand burned with glowing coals.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How I suffer in far-off Meshech.It pains me to live in distant Kedar.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am tired of livingamong people who hate peace.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem.  I look up to the mountains\u2014does
        my help come from there?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My help comes from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,who made heaven
        and earth!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will not let you stumble;the one who watches over you will not
        slumber.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Indeed, he who watches over Israelnever slumbers or sleeps.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>himself watches over you!The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        stands beside you as your protective shade.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The sun will not harm you by day,nor the moon at night.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> keeps you from all harmand watches
        over your life.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem. A psalm of David.  I
        was glad when they said to me,\u201CLet us go to the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And now here we are,standing inside your gates, O Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Jerusalem is a well-built city;its seamless walls cannot be breached.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All the tribes of Israel\u2014the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        people\u2014make their pilgrimage here.They come to give thanks to the name
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,as the law requires of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Here stand the thrones where judgment is given,the thrones of the
        dynasty of David.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Pray for peace in Jerusalem.May all who love this city prosper.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O Jerusalem, may there be peace within your wallsand prosperity in
        your palaces.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the sake of my family and friends, I will say,\u201CMay you have
        peace.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem.  I lift my eyes to you,O
        God, enthroned in heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We keep looking to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God for his
        mercy,just as servants keep their eyes on their master,as a slave girl watches
        her mistress for the slightest signal.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Have mercy on us, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have mercy,for we
        have had our fill of contempt.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem. A psalm of David.  What
        if the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had not been on our side?Let all Israel
        repeat:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What if the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had not been on our sidewhen
        people attacked us?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They would have swallowed us alivein their burning anger.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The waters would have engulfed us;a torrent would have overwhelmed
        us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, the raging waters of their furywould have overwhelmed our very
        lives.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,who did not let their teeth
        tear us apart!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We escaped like a bird from a hunter\u2019s trap.The trap is broken,
        and we are free!  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem.  Those who trust in the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> are as secure as Mount Zion;they will not be
        defeated but will endure forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Just as the mountains surround Jerusalem,so the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        surrounds his people, both now and forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked will not rule the land of the godly,for then the godly
        might be tempted to do wrong.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, do good to those who are good,whose
        hearts are in tune with you.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem.  When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        brought back his exiles to Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]]it was like a dream!  '
      comments:
      - number: '126:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "We were filled with laughter,and we sang for joy.And the other nations
        said,\u201CWhat amazing things the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has done for
        them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has done amazing things for
        us!What joy!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Restore our fortunes, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,as streams renew
        the desert.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who plant in tearswill harvest with shouts of joy.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem. A psalm of Solomon. 
        Unless the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> builds a house,the work of the builders
        is wasted.Unless the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> protects a city,guarding
        it with sentries will do no good.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is useless for you to work so hardfrom early morning until late
        at night,anxiously working for food to eat;for God gives rest to his loved
        ones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Children are a gift from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;they are
        a reward from him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Children born to a young manare like arrows in a warrior\u2019s hands.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem.  How joyful are those
        who fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014all who follow his ways!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will enjoy the fruit of your labor.How joyful and prosperous
        you will be!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your wife will be like a fruitful grapevine,flourishing within your
        home.Your children will be like vigorous young olive treesas they sit around
        your table.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s blessingfor those
        who fear him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> continually bless you from Zion.May
        you see Jerusalem prosper as long as you live.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem.  From my earliest youth
        my enemies have persecuted me.Let all Israel repeat this:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'From my earliest youth my enemies have persecuted me,but they have
        never defeated me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My back is covered with cuts,as if a farmer had plowed long furrows.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is good;he has cut me free from
        the ropes of the ungodly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May all who hate Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]be turned back in shameful
        defeat.  '
      comments:
      - number: '129:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'May they be as useless as grass on a rooftop,turning yellow when
        only half grown,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'ignored by the harvester,despised by the binder.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem.  From the depths of despair,
        O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,I call for your help.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Hear my cry, O Lord.Pay attention to my prayer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, if you kept a record of our sins,who,
        O Lord, could ever survive?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you offer forgiveness,that we might learn to fear you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am counting on the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;yes, I am counting
        on him.I have put my hope in his word.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I long for the Lordmore than sentries long for the dawn,yes, more
        than sentries long for the dawn.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O Israel, hope in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;for with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        there is unfailing love.His redemption overflows.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem. A psalm of David.   
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, my heart is not proud;my eyes are not haughty.I
        don\u2019t concern myself with matters too greator too awesome for me to
        grasp.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Instead, I have calmed and quieted myself,like a weaned child who
        no longer cries for its mother\u2019s milk.Yes, like a weaned child is my
        soul within me.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem.    <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        remember Davidand all that he suffered.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He made a solemn promise to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.He vowed
        to the Mighty One of Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '132:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Jacob; </b>also in 132:5. See note on 44:4.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will not go home;I will not let myself rest.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will not let my eyes sleepnor close my eyelids in slumber  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "until I find a place to build a house for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,a
        sanctuary for the Mighty One of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We heard that the Ark was in Ephrathah;then we found it in the distant
        countryside of Jaar.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let us go to the sanctuary of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;let
        us worship at the footstool of his throne.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Arise, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and enter your resting place,along
        with the Ark, the symbol of your power.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'May your priests be clothed in godliness;may your loyal servants
        sing for joy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the sake of your servant David,do not reject the king you have
        anointed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> swore an oath to Davidwith a promise
        he will never take back:\u201CI will place one of your descendantson your
        throne.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If your descendants obey the terms of my covenantand the laws that
        I teach them,then your royal linewill continue forever and ever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has chosen Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]];he
        has desired it for his home.  '
      comments:
      - number: '132:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is my resting place forever,\u201D he said.\u201CI will
        live here, for this is the home I desired.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will bless this city and make it prosperous;I will satisfy its
        poor with food.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will clothe its priests with godliness;its faithful servants will
        sing for joy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Here I will increase the power of David;my anointed one will be a
        light for my people.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem. A psalm of David.  How
        wonderful and pleasant it iswhen brothers live together in harmony!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For harmony is as precious as the anointing oilthat was poured over
        Aaron\u2019s head,that ran down his beardand onto the border of his robe.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'A song for pilgrims ascending to Jerusalem.  Oh, praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        all you servants of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,you who serve at night
        in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lift your hands toward the sanctuary,and praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Praise the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Praise
        him, you who serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'you who serve in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,in
        the courts of the house of our God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is good;celebrate his lovely name with music.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has chosen Jacob for himself,Israel
        for his own special treasure.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I know the greatness of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014that
        our Lord is greater than any other god.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> does whatever pleases himthroughout
        all heaven and earth,and on the seas and in their depths.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He causes the clouds to rise over the whole earth.He sends the lightning
        with the rainand releases the wind from his storehouses.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He destroyed the firstborn in each Egyptian home,both people and
        animals.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He performed miraculous signs and wonders in Egyptagainst Pharaoh
        and all his people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He struck down great nationsand slaughtered mighty kings\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sihon king of the Amorites,Og king of Bashan,and all the kings of
        Canaan.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He gave their land as an inheritance,a special possession to his
        people Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your name, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, endures forever;your fame,
        O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, is known to every generation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will give justice to his peopleand
        have compassion on his servants.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The idols of the nations are merely things of silver and gold,shaped
        by human hands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have mouths but cannot speak,and eyes but cannot see.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have ears but cannot hear,and mouths but cannot breathe.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And those who make idols are just like them,as are all who trust
        in them.  '
      comments: []
